title: cape cod fish chowder
directions: Simmer fish in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Drain off and reserve broth. Remove skin and bones from fish.
Saute the diced pork in a large pot until crisp. Saute onions and pork fat until golden brown. Add fish, celery, potatoes and bay leaf.
Measure reserved fish broth, plus enough boiling water to make 3 cups liquid.
Add to pot and simmer 30 minutes. Add milk and butter and simmer for an additional 5 minutes or until well heated.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together; add egg yolks and mix in the dry ingredients one by one, alternating with butter and milk. Add the coconut, pecans and cherries. Fold in the egg whites. Pour the mixture into 3 (8 x 10-inch) round cake pans and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. Layer the cake with the frosting and decorate with well drained cherries and pecan halves.

title: mushroom-dill chicken rolls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir cut margarine into hot water until melted.
Add stuffing crumbs, red pepper and egg; stir until moist.
Spoon stuffing evenly over chicken.
Roll tightly; secure with toothpicks.
Place in greased 9-inch square baking dish. Brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cooked through.
Heat soup, water and dill in saucepan.
Serve over chicken.

title: betty's banana drop cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix the bananas, mashed with a fork and the eggs.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and bananas.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt and mix well.
Add nuts, raisins and, if needed, a bit more flour.
Drop on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Remove from pans with broad spatula while warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, sugar, milk, salt and butter.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar, orange juice, pineapple juice and kool-aid together.
Put in large punch bowl.
Add ice ring and ginger ale. This is a fast punch that is really good.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasonings and soup.
Heat slightly.
Add 3 or 4 slices of cheese.
Heat until melted.
Put on buns open face and put under broiler until cheese bubbles.
Also makes good pudgy pies for campers.

title: honolulu punch
directions: Combine
fruit
juices,
frozen concentrates and sugar; chill thoroughly.
Add chilled ginger ale and carbonated water just before
serving;
pour
over
large block of ice in punch bowl. If
desired,
float
a
flower on ice and garnish punch with mint leaves.
Small
pieces
of
dry ice may be added to chilled punch in bowl; the punch will have white smoke rising from bowl and will bubble in an unusual way.
Yield:
35 to 40 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheet.

Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and lemon juice in large bowl. Beat on low speed; add nuts. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet 1-inch apart. Bake 6 to 7 minutes or until light brown. Cool 1 minute. Dust with 10x sugar.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk, butter and eggs until blended.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring until flour mixture is just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filled 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 18 muffins.

title: creole gumbo
directions: Heat lard in good sized iron pot.
Chop onions, garlic, bell pepper and celery; fry.
Brown with flour.
Add seafood and water according to pot.
Add thyme and bay leaves and let simmer.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together and drop in patterns on hot griddle.
Fry until brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: waxy pecan cake(no fat)
directions: Let sugar set over egg whites until melted.
Stir.
Add flour and baking powder.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: french meat pies
directions: Place beef, pork, onion, salt and pepper in a deep pan.
Add water to cover meat.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and lower heat to simmer.
Continue cooking for about 6 hours, making sure that there is always just enough water to cover the meat.
After 6 hours, season to taste.
Crush crackers and add to the meat, a little at a time, until thickened.
Prepare pie crusts (enough for 4 pie tins). Fill with meat mixture and add top crust.
Bake at 325° until top crust is golden brown.
Makes 4 large pies.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk and beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers.
Spread half of pudding mixture on crackers.
Cover pudding with crackers. Spread remaining pudding on crackers.
Cover with crackers. Spread frosting on top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: dressing
directions: Add enough broth to make soupy.
Stir well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
May add a can of oysters.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and chocolate together.
Add the milk, butter, beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Put in unbaked pie shell and brown shell. Makes 2 pies.

title: allie's chicken goulash
directions: Cook chicken, onion and garlic in margarine until onion is wilted.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour, sour cream and noodles.
Cook and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Stir to coat.
In a separate bowl, beat together oil, milk and eggs. Add pumpkin. Combine liquid and dry ingredients until moistened.
Pour into 30 paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick removes clean.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef, bell pepper, garlic powder, onion, salt and pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Pour into baking dish.
Add tomato paste, soup and Italian seasoning.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until biscuits are done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into a baking dish.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Toss hot spaghetti with olive oil.
Combine eggs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Stir into spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti mixture into prepared pie plate and form into a crust.
Spread Ricotta cheese over spaghetti.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan and cool 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Brown together beef, onion, parsley, salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Make pie crusts.
Mix together bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.

title: best margaritas
directions: In a blender with ice, add all ingredients together. Blend and enjoy!

title: surprise cheese puffs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Drain olives on paper towels.
Shape a thin layer of cheese mixture around each olive.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(May use cocktail onions instead of olives.)

title: delicious faux lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a nonstick skillet, cook hamburger meat, onion and green pepper until no longer pink; drain.
Blend in tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Keep warm.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in cups of boiling water and add pie filling. Add pine apples; with the juice.
Chill until set.

title: apple pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, cook on medium-high heat the desired number of pork chops (our family prefers thin-sliced boneless chops) until browned on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 cup apple juice over chops.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer approximately 45 minutes until pork chops are glazed.
Turn pork chops over and glaze the other side with remaining juice in the pan, about 1 to 2 minutes.
If desired, serve with slices of cooking apple (any variety).

title: whole wheat macaroni russian style
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Saute in butter the remaining ingredients.
Boil 2 cups raw whole wheat macaroni in salted water until done.
Drain and butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 pint of orange sherbet (while still warm).
Stir until melted.
Add mandarin oranges (drained) and the pineapple with the juice.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, onion, chives, green pepper, pepper and sour cream.
Put in an 8-inch pie plate. Sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped walnuts or pecans on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.
Can be frozen, uncooked.
Double ingredients for 9 to 10-inch pie plate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer and sprinkle pepper on top.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: party hawaiian chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place, skin side down, in baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°, turn chicken and bake an additional 1/2 hour.

title: miracle pie
directions: Mix crackers and walnuts; set aside.
Combine egg whites, sugar, vanilla and baking powder and add to cracker mixture.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool about 6 hours.
Top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nuts (makes its own crust).

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: In a bowl, combine carrots and raisins. Mix thoroughly.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt and lemon juice. Stir to mix well.
Pour over carrot-raisin mixture and mix well. Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: frozen cream cheese salad
directions: Soften cream cheese; add salad dressing.
Blend together.
Add pineapple and cherries.
Beat whipping cream.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add marshmallows.
Put in mold or cupcake pans.
Cover and freeze.

title: tuna cheese coneys
directions: Chop eggs and add all the ingredients; fill buns.
Wrap in foil; heat 30 minutes at 250°.
Serve hot.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry in a skillet until crisp. Drain off some of the fat.
Meantime, mix in a pint jar the flour, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Fill jar with water and shake well to mix.
Pour this into skillet with bacon and add milk until desired thickness.
Cook and stir until thick.
Pour over spinach, lettuce or endive.
Hard-boiled eggs may be chopped in.

title: mixed fruit ambrosia(dessert on the grill)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pound cake and sour cream until well mixed.
Place mixture in center of an 18-inch square of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Bring edges together and crimp securely.
Bring opposite sides together; fold and crimp.

title: cheesy hash brown potato casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: christmas fun for the kids
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients until well mixed. You may have to add more flour if too wet or more water if too dry. Flour working area and roll dough out until 1/4 inch thick.
Dip cookie cutter in the flour and cut out ornaments.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Use the end of the paint brush to punch a hole in the top to hang by.
Decorate with paints, glitter and ribbon.

title: yellow cake and pineapple upside down cake
directions: Blend
together
thoroughly
Crisco and sugar; add eggs and blend;
add
flour and milk alternately; add vanilla; beat well. Bake
in
a
moderate 350° oven
for 30 to 35 minutes, 325° for glass
dish.
Makes
2 (9-inch) layers, 1 1/2-inches deep.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Spread 1/3
cup room temperature hot fudge topping over the bottom of pie crust.
Place in freezer to chill.
Meanwhile, soften ice cream and mix with peanut butter.
Spoon into pie crust and freeze several hours or overnight.
Cover with plastic wrap when firm.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread on plate with edges.
Spread over mixture the chopped vegetables.
Top with shredded cheese. Serve with nacho chips.

title: easy asparagus side dish
directions: Drain asparagus and arrange to cover bottom of greased Pyrex or Corning Ware pie baking dish. Combine milk and beaten egg. Pour over asparagus. Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes until set and lightly browned.

title: chew pecan cookie squares
directions: Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Stir in flour which has been mixed with baking powder and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle remaining pecans and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Roll chicken in egg mixture, then crumbs.
Then brown chicken.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onion and seasonings.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese and additional oregano leaves.

title: sparkling strawberry spritzer
directions: Place strawberries in a electric blender and process until smooth. Pour strawberry puree into punch bowl or pitcher and stir in juice, then club soda. Serve immediately. Garnish with fresh strawberries and mint leaves. Makes 14 servings.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Make Italian dressing mix according to package directions; pour over veggies.
Allow to marinate for 2 hours.
This salad keeps very well.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans about 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 2 (9-inch) cake pans; cool.
Crumble one layer of cake into bottom of a large punch bowl.
Combine one package of pudding mix and 2 1/2 cups milk and pour over cake immediately.
Spread half of pineapple over pudding.
Spread 1 can of cherry pie filling over pineapple and spread half of Cool Whip over pie filling.
Repeat layers. Sprinkle with pecans.
Garnish with cherries.

title: layered dip(mexican)
directions: Layer the bean dip and avocados.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and garlic salt.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix.
Layer sour cream mixture, tomatoes, onions, olives, cheese dip and cheese.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, then 7-Up and vanilla.
It usually takes 10 minutes of beating (this makes it good).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May take 5 to 10 minutes less, depending on oven.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla wafer crumbs; beat until blended.
Press mixture evenly into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan lined with wax paper.

title: erminia's caramelized custard
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
You will need a heavy-duty aluminum mold that will set evenly in a roaster pan.
A Bundt cake type mold is not suitable.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Combine green beans, green peas, pimento, onion and celery in large bowl.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and salt in small bowl.
Pour over green bean mixture; toss to mix.
Chill for 24 hours.
Drain before serving.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Bring pineapple and
sugar to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add
to cooked mixture; add lemon juice.
Chop cherries and blend with pineapple.	Combine everything, except Cool Whip, and refrigerate until thickened.
Add Cool Whip and congeal until firm.
This
recipe may also be frozen and works well in small molds.

title: very berry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: greenthread navajo tea(traditional)
directions: Gather the plant along open plains and slopes.
Tie the plants into small bundles and dry them in the shade.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour gradually.
Add flavoring.
Last, slowly add 7-Up.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(Make sure pan is greased and floured.)
Do not use any other carbonated drink.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine taco seasoning, sour cream and cream cheese with mixer.
Spread into a lasagna or cake pan.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with Doritos or Tortilla Chips.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Cook everything together except vanilla, stirring constantly. Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose one too young and tender and take only those that have been reared in good moral atmosphere.
Some insist upon keeping them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties have been made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience.
Well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste.
Then wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream and they will keep for years.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Mix in a bowl all ingredients, except chocolate chips, pat out in a 12 x 12-inch (or so) pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over crust.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash in salted (1/4 cup) water about 7 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add soup, sour cream, carrot, onion and pimentos. Put 1/2 package of stuffing in melted butter or margarine and white pepper, mix well.
Place all this mixture in one large or two small casseroles and top with remaining half package of stuffing.
Place in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
This can be refrigerated or frozen and baked later.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and mix together next 5 ingredients.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish, layer chips, chicken and soup. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Cook at 325° for glass dish.
Add cheese on top.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Slice apples.
Wrap apples in flakes of biscuit dough.
Pinch around edges.
Layer in casserole dish.
Pour water and butter over apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples until well covered.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken; put skin side down in pan.
Bake for 35 minutes, then turn pieces over and bake until done.

title: international twist
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large pot of boiling water, cook pasta according to directions.
Drain.
Meanwhile, saute kielbasa, peppers and onion in a large, nonstick skillet.
Add salsa, kidney beans, tomato sauce, olives and taco seasoning and cook until the vegetables are softened (about 7 minutes).
Grease a 10-inch glass pie pan with nonstick spray.
Pour the pasta mixture into the pan; top with half of the shredded cheeses.

title: grandma ponden's coconut pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell of favorite crust.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mandarin spice muffins
directions: Drain oranges on paper towel.
Sift flour before measuring. Sift into large bowl: flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, allspice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in shortening to fine crumbs.
Combine egg and milk and add to dry mixture until flour is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until blended.
Pour over oats.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Toss noodles and onions and layer in large casserole.
Add a layer of shrimp.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over shrimp. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cauliflower delite
directions: Wash and trim cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Precook them in boiling water with salt added for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine flour and bread crumbs in plastic bag.
Add cauliflower and shake to coat well.
Fry in butter until golden brown, turning frequently.
Serve promptly.

title: pretzel surprise
directions: Melt margarine and mix with pretzels, sugar and nuts.
Press into pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: seven-layer dinner
directions: In a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, celery, meat, onion, green pepper and tomatoes. Sprinkle potato and beef layers with salt and pepper.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 2 hours, or until potatoes are tender. Add cheese about 15 minutes before casserole is ready to remove from oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Grease your mixing bowl, then add all of the ingredients.
Mix with a spatula only.
Pour into a greased but not floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and finely chopped nuts, if desired. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pickle-roll-em-ups
directions: Spread one side of each ham slice with one tablespoon cream cheese.
Place one pickle on edge of each ham slice.
Roll ham slice around pickle.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut each into 6 slices. Serve with assorted vegetable dippers, cheese, olives, etc.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: to replenish starter
directions: For the Sourdough Starter with Yeast, add equal amounts of warm water and flour with 1 tsp. sugar.
Stir until smooth, cover with cheesecloth and allow to bubble overnight.
Replace lid and store in refrigerator.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in saucepan.
Add just enough water to cover rice and cook for 20 minutes, then drain.
In same pan to cook pudding, add 1 quart milk and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Then simmer for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.
Place rice pudding into container or pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add soda in water.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add all other ingredients. Fold with spoon.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips or cubes; dust with flour and pepper. Brown meat in skillet in butter.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic; brown slightly.
Stri in broth.
Cover; cook for 1 hour, or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Gradually blend in sour cream; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Combine with noodles.

title: brownies
directions: In mixing bowl, mix sugar, cocoa, butter and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs; blend well.
Add flour last.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Place fruit atop butter.
Combine milk, flour and sugar.
Pour batter atop fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: simple peanut butter cookies
directions: Separate egg whites; beat with mixer on medium for 2 minutes. Slowly add sugar.
Beat on high until soft peaks form.
Mix peanut butter into mixture by hand.
Drop spoonful of mix onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cookies will be soft.
Let cool, then enjoy.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all together and place in 9-inch square pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 to 6.
Double this recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine and chocolate chips and stir in peanut butter until creamy.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Mix until well coated. Place powdered sugar in plastic bag.
Add cereal and shake until well coated.
Put in bowl and place in freezer until set.

title: homemade sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar to shortening.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and mix/blend together.
Separately mix all dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with the sugar mixture slowly.
Drop one spoonful (1 cookie) at a time onto a cookie sheet.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple (undrained) in a large bowl with dry pudding.
Gradually stir in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Refrigerate.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: taco salad
directions: First Layer:
On a large, flat dish, layer sour cream mixed with 1 package of seasoning mix.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour with dry ingredients; add egg, melted shortening and orange juice.
Combine only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Turn into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and Jell-O together.
Add oil, eggs, water and strawberries.
Beat 300 strokes and pour into greased and floured tube pan or 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake tube pan for 1 hour or 25 to 30 minutes for cake pans.
Test to make sure cake is done.

title: peanut butter refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together peanut butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time; add dry ingredients sifted together. Form dough into a 2-inch roll and let stand in refrigerator until firm. Slice into 1/4-inch slices. Place on cookie sheet; press with floured fork across centers. Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Remove crust from bread. Cube bread and soak in margarine. Add cheese, red pepper, mustard, milk and salt. Beat egg whites and fold in mixture. Pour in buttered rectangle dish. Set aside for 12 hours in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake(low-fat)
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or glass casserole dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake using 3 Egg Beaters (3/4 cup).
While cake is baking, mix sugar and pineapple in a saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove cake from oven; prick top with a fork.
Pour pineapple mixture over the top of cake; cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding with skim milk as directed on package.
Spread on top of cooled cake.
Slice bananas; place over top of pudding.
Spread prepared Dream Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle Grape-Nuts cereal over the top.
Slice the cherries in half; place on top of Dream Whip.
Distribute evenly over the top.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serves 20.

title: short-cut chili dinner
directions: Prepare chili according to package directions; stir in pinto beans and pepperoni slices.
Add water; simmer over low heat about 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Serve with shredded Mozzarella cheese and corn chips.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls or pizza crust on pizza pan or small cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°; let cool.
Mix sour cream and Hidden Valley dressing mix together and spread over the cooled crust.
Sprinkle the broccoli, cauliflower and carrots over the sour cream mixture, heavily.
Garnish with grated Mozzarella cheese and black olives.
Let chill one hour before serving.
Slice in small pieces for appetizers or larger pieces for a salad type luncheon.

title: bacon bats
directions: Grind
or crumble bacon, cheese and onion together; stir in seasonings.
Toast bread on one side under broiler;
spread untoasted side with filling; cut in any desired shape.
Arrange on cookie
sheet;
place under broiler until bubbly and brown. Serve immediately.
These may be spread in advance and broiled before serving.
A
fine
filling	for
children's
open-faced sandwiches.
Freezes well.

title: a meal in minutes
directions: Brown meat and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook in electric skillet for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Line muffin tins with muffin cups.
Divide batter equally (12 muffins).
Bake 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Alternate layers of soup mixture, onions and beans in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake another 5 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: In a medium bowl, blend the cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until smooth.
Thoroughly blend in caramel topping and cover. Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve as a dip for fresh fruit. Is especially good with Granny Smith apple slices.

title: granny's apple cobbler
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a glass dish.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip egg yolks until light in color. Blend in sweetened condensed milk and lime juice.
Pour filling into crust and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and let cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate overnight.
To serve top with sweetened whip cream.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix sugar with 2 cups warm water and flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Let sit in glass jar, covered with cloth for 5 days.
Refrigerate mixture 3 to 5 days, then begin to feed with Sourdough Potato Feed.

title: crazy mixed up cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the liquid ingredients together well.
Gradually add the liquid mixture to the dry ingredients, stirring as you go.
Grease and flour one oblong pan or two 9 1/2-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick in the center comes out clean.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: grandma mables' shortbread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat well.
Add about 4 1/4 cups of flour slowly and mix until dough cracks (use hands if necessary).
Roll out 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Decorate with cut up cherries.
Bake in slow oven, 275° to 300°, until medium brown, 20 to 35 minutes. Cool on rack.
Store tightly covered.
May freeze.
Can be made in food processor.

title: easy breaded fish
directions: Dip fish fillets into bottled French dressing.
Roll in crushed round-type crackers.
Arrange on plate or microwave rack. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes per pound.

title: betty jean's one dish meal
directions: *Mix cheese with remaining ingredients and retain some to put on top after mixture is poured into casserole baking dish.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In saucepan, heat marshmallows and milk over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until marshmallows are melted (or melt in microwave); cool.
In small saucepan, combine gelatin and water; heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Combine cooled marshmallow mixture and gelatin; gradually beat into softened cream cheese.
Drain berries, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to equal 1 cup liquid.
Stir syrup into gelatin mixture; chill until partially set.
Whip gelatin mixture; fold in berries.
Whip cream and fold into whipped gelatin mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill until set.
Trim with more whipped cream and berries.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Boil meat until red color is gone; drain.
Mix meat with spaghetti sauce and sugar; simmer on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, boil noodles until done.
Drain and mix with sauce and coat well.
Put mixture in a Pyrex baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread apples in 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle with mixture of water, cinnamon, and salt.
Mix sugar, flour, and butter.
Work together until crumbly and then spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream oil and sugars. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients and mix into egg mixture. Add chocolate chips. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix baking powder and flour.
Gradually add flour mixture to egg mixture, alternating with cream.
Pour into 10-inch spring-form pan.
Peel apples and cut into wedges.
Arrange wedges in a fan on top of batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Grated cheese may be added to the top before baking if you like.
Double the recipe for a large casserole.

title: lime fruit dip
directions: Beat eggs; combine in top of double boiler with sugar, cornstarch and limeade concentrate.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in food coloring. Cool.
Whip cream and fold into cooled limeade mixture.
Transfer to bowl or individual serving dishes; serve with fresh fruit and berries.

title: english wassail
directions: Combine cider, sugar, undiluted lemonade and orange juice in a large kettle.
Heat to simmering.
Add spices.
Cover.
Heat to simmering and leave for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Add spirits if desired (apple brandy or rum).
Some folks start with tea or cranberry juice, others with cider.
The cider beverage has the virtue of outstanding aroma and can "perfume" the whole house. This is good to come into on a cold day.

title: ground beef and spaghetti
directions: Brown meat with onion and chopped bell pepper.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and macaroni; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans as directed.
Drain.
Add other ingredients, cook 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven or until hot.
Add French fried onions and brown.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including dry gelatin.
Chill before serving.
Coconut and/or nuts may be added.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, chicken and sour cream.
Dip tortillas into hot oil.
Spoon 3 teaspoons of chicken cream mixture into tortillas. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of cheese on top of chicken cream mixture. Roll up.
Place into oblong dish, seam side down.
Tortillas should fit snugly.
Pour rest of chicken cream mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put beef in large pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Serve in soup bowls sprinkled with grated cheese.
Serve with cornbread or corn chips.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Cook pepper and garlic until tender in oil.
Blend soup and pineapple juice.
Add chicken, soy sauce and pineapple.
Heat and top with almonds.
Serve over rice.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick margarine and set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Alternate flour and soda with buttermilk.
Add candy bars and butter mixture.
Add pecans and mix.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together
oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add
all the other ingredients except the nuts.
Add nuts last. Makes
loaves.
Bake
in 350° oven until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Measure sugar, oil
and pumpkin into large mixing bowl. Beat well at medium
speed.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well after each	addition.
Add	flour,	baking	powder, soda, cinnamon and salt
(sifted),
small	amounts at a time, mixing well after each
addition.
Fold
in
raisins	and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan lined with wax paper on bottom. Level batter with back of spoon.
Bake in moderate 350° oven about 1
hour
and
15 minutes or until done.
Serve plain or with orange powdered sugar glaze.

title: turkey and white bean chili
directions: Cook turkey, onion and 3/4 cup of the broth in a 3-quart pan over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in remaining broth, cumin, oregano, chili powder, red pepper, garlic and green chilies.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in bell pepper and beans.
Cook uncovered over low heat, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve chili topped with sour cream, salsa and cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage set for about 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: meat loaf chowder
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, sausage, egg, salt and pepper and make into small meatballs.
Cook in a 350° oven until done.
Boil water and add soup mix.
Let simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add meatballs, tomatoes, kidney beans and carrots.
Simmer all ingredients for 15 minutes, covered.
Add 1 cup of Minute rice. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will also need 12 sticks.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine juice of lemons, egg yellows, milk and salt together. Hand beat until thick and smooth.
Pour in vanilla wafer crust. Make meringue from whites of egg.
Bake until brown.

title: sea foam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and heat 1 cup juice to boiling. Pour over Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Cool. Mix cream cheese and 2 tablespoons cream until smooth. Add gelatin mixture and beat well until blended. Chill until partially thickened. Fold in pears and whipped cream. Pour into a 1-quart ring or star-shaped mold and chill.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine margarine and sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Serve hot.
Yields about 1 1/4 dozen.

title: cold mango relish
directions: Put in crock and store in cold place.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream shortening; add confectioners sugar (gradually) and almond extract. Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk to dry ingredients.
Blend together; add cherries and walnuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool; smooth top with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and confectioners sugar.

title: cap'n crunch cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Mix Cap'n Crunch cereal, Rice Krispies cereal, marshmallows and pecans in another bowl. Add chocolate to cereal mixture.
Stir.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: chicken breast with dried beef
directions: Line large flat 2 to 3-quart casserole with dried beef.
Place in oven to dry out beef.
Roll each chicken breast and wrap with slice of bacon.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Combine soup and sour cream, pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover casserole with foil and bake 3 hours in 300° oven.
Remove foil for at least 1/2 hour to brown.
Don't add any salt.

title: chicken or turkey strata
directions: First Layer:
Put 1/2 of bread crumbs in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: randy's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Brown sausage in frying pan and drain.
Slice cheese and cut up tomatoes. Combine cooked macaroni, browned sausage, chopped tomatoes and cheese slices in covered casserole dish.
Place in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Brown carrots and onion in butter.

title: red beans
directions: Brown and drain all meats. Brown onions and peppers. Add all ingredients and cook slow.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in a microwave dish. Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stop and stir.
Cook for 3 more minutes.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cook for 1 more minute. Add soda and stir gently.
Pour quickly onto greased cookie sheet and allow to cool.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: fruit magic cobbler pie
directions: Melt margarine and pour into casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and milk.
Pour into melted margarine, but do not stir.
Add fruit on top, but do not stir.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: old fashioned mocha shake
directions: In blender container, combine milk, Choco-bake and vanilla. Process at high speed until smooth, about 15 seconds.
Add ice cream, blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: arizona quiche
directions: Spread Jack cheese and half of Cheddar cheese evenly over bottom of partially baked pie crust.
Put diced chilies over cheese.
Combine half and half, eggs, salt and cumin.
Pour carefully into pie crust.
Top with rest of Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Shake gently to test for doneness. Serves 6.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger and onions in pan.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Using a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer ingredients in this order:
noodles, hamburger, sauce, cottage cheese, noodles, hamburger, sauce, mushrooms, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, hamburger, sauce, Cheddar cheese and noodles. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover with aluminum foil before baking.

title: party brownies
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well. Stir in cocoa.
Add flour and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut in squares when cool.
Ice lightly with confectioners sugar mixed with cream to make a thin paste.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed until creamy smooth.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and mix in thoroughly with a fork.
Add liquid to make soft dough.

title: bbq meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients and roll into balls.
Place in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Cover with sauce and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour 1/2 of corn meal mixture into heated and greased 10-inch iron skillet (or may use 8 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish, buttered). Then put browned hamburger, onions, banana pepper and cheese (in this order) and pour the rest of the corn meal mixture over this.

title: glenda's sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins; peel and mash.
Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, coconut, eggs, vanilla and 1/4 stick margarine.
Put into a casserole dish.

title: very blueberry pie
directions: Rinse and drain blueberries.
Make a smooth paste of water, flour and salt.
Boil 1 cup of blueberries with the sugar and water.
Add the flour paste.
Stir until it thickens.
Remove from stove and cool.
When cool, add the remaining blueberries.
Put into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
When cold, garnish with sweetened whipped cream or whipped topping.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine. Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
In large mixer bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased sheet pan.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched. In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and Eagle Brand.
Stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs.
Add melted butter.
Add rest of ingredients, vinegar last.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Use 2 non-deep pie shells.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Stir in currants.
Combine eggs, 1 3/4 cups buttermilk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients until flour is moistened.
Add 1/4 cup more buttermilk if needed.
Batter should be thick and with small lumps but not dry.
Turn batter into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and allow to cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: quinton's quick cornbread
directions: Prepare cornbread as directed on the box.
Mix cheeses and chilies into the batter.
Pour into greased pan as directed and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: randy's broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Place half of stuffing mix in a greased 2-quart casserole. In a saute pan, melt margarine and add celery, onion and broccoli, cooking until tender.
Add chicken, rice, cheese and soup.
Spread over stuffing mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Cover and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes more.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen chocolate bananas
directions: Put chopped peanuts into bowl.
Put chocolate pieces into skillet on low heat, stirring until all chocolate is melted.
Peel bananas and cut in half.
Dip bananas and roll in chocolate until covered.
Roll into the peanuts.
Put bananas on waxed paper and put in freezer until firm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large baking bowl.
Slice onion on top.
Cover with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered.
If covered, bake 30 more minutes.

title: poached peaches supreme
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, microwave water with tea bags at 100% power 2 minutes or until very hot.
Do not boil.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove bags.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make out in 2 rolls; wrap in foil. Let stand 24
hours in refrigerator in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy tortilla beef bake
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in soup.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups tortilla chips in a greased shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with beef mixture, salsa and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with the remaining chips.
Bake 3 minutes longer or until chips are lightly toasted.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: black bean and rice salad(vegetarian)
directions: Combine rice, black beans, parsley and tomato in a large bowl. Add dressing and lemon or lime juice; toss lightly.
Arrange on a bed or lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in a large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add corn flakes cereal.
Stir until well coated.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix with 1/2 gallon whole milk and beaten eggs.
Cook until it forms a custard.
Be sure to cook on low heat and stir to keep from scorching.
If it lumps at all, strain through strainer after you have added Carnation and flavoring.
Let cool and then freeze.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Crumble ground beef in a large bowl; mix in dry seasoning of your own choice.
Add eggs, bread crumbs and tomato sauce; mix well.
Cut onion into quarters and place 1 quarter in each corner of meat loaf baking pan.
Add meat mixture.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain grease from pan every 1/2 hour or as needed.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
First layer:
Mix 1 package Jell-O with 2 teaspoons Knox gelatine and 1 cup hot water.
Cool.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in thin slices; fry until done and place in casserole dish.
Shred enough cabbage to cover potatoes, then pour the soups over potatoes and cabbage.
Top with your choice of meat. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Do not remove foil until taken from oven.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and powdered garlic cheese salad dressing mix.
Add other ingredients.

title: monkey bread
directions: Beat well after each addition.
Let rise until double in bulk. Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip into melted oleo (1 stick) and place into tube pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angie's shrimp dip
directions: Heat cream cheese and tomato soup until cheese melts.
Mix gelatin and water; add to cheese mixture.
Heat on low heat for 5 minutes.
Add celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Add cooked shrimp. Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion; cook with ground beef.
In a large saucepan, add all ingredients except cheese and bring to a boil.
Mix ground beef and onion with sauce.
Layer soft shells in a long baking pan.
Pour sauce and ground beef over it.
Layer cheese over sauce.
Repeat again.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400° or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Cool and eat.

title: donna's lazy woman's cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the sugar, flour, salt, cocoa and baking soda.
Make 3 holes in the dry ingredients.
Pour oil, vanilla and vinegar in each hole.
Pour water over all and stir with fork until smooth. Pour into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yam biscuits
directions: Combine yams, butter and egg. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Blend into yam mixture. Place on a well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: cranberry orange sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine cornstarch, lemon peel, cloves and salt.
Stir in orange and lemon juice until smooth.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly until sauce is smooth and thick. Stir in cranberry sauce and heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot or cold over turkey or ham.
Good for holidays.

title: basic yeast dough
directions: Place yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 cup warm water in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine milk, 1/4 cup sugar, shortening and salt in saucepan and heat to just below a boil. Cool to lukewarm. Add 1 1/2 cups flour; stir well.
Add egg and yeast; blend well. Gradually sift another 2 cups flour until batter begins to turn loose from the sides of the bowl and follow the spoon around the bowl.
Turn dough out on well floured surface and knead. Place in well oiled bowl and place in warm place until it doubles in size.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead. Shape into biscuits or loaf and let rise again until double in size. Bake at desired temperature, about 350° to 400°, depending on thickness.

title: seven layer magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed. Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Beat all the ingredients until creamy and fluffy.

title: elephant stew
directions: After elephant is cleaned, add seasonings.
Cook in a very large pot outdoors.
Invite all the friends and relatives.
Cook elephant for 4 to 5 days, or until tender.
If everybody shows up, add cup up rabbit, but only as a last resort, because most people don't like "hare" in their stew.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place large cooking bag in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shake flour in bag; add tomato sauce, water, bouillon, salt and pepper in bag and mix.
Add roast and mushrooms.
Peel and quarter vegetables; add to bag.
Turn gently over and over.
Close and tie bag; make 6 slits in bag.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mash garlic cloves.
Add salt to make a paste.
Add lemon juice and oil.
Add chicken and marinate for 1 hour or more. Grill chicken over low heat until done.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Cut up breasts; put in a 4 x 13-inch or larger deep dish pan. Pour soup over chicken and mix.
Place slices of Swiss cheese on top to cover.
Then top with stuffing.
Drizzle the melted butter on top of that.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir in cream, corn syrup and salt.
Add butter.
Cook, covered, on High 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until sugar is dissolved and sauce is thickened.
Add vanilla and stir.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes; add margarine.
Add eggs, milk, cream, cinnamon and sugar.
Pour into casserole dish.
Put marshmallows on top; with fork, very lightly dip down in mixture until they are wet. Combine brown sugar and pecans; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Put small pats of butter on top.
Cook at 325° for about 1 hour.
Top will be crusty.
Serves 8.

title: noodle and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles in rapidly boiling salted water for about 8 to 10 minutes or until tender but not soft.
Drain well and keep warm. Mash cottage cheese with cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix this with the noodles and season with salt and pepper.
Mix in lightly scallions or chives and turn the mixture into a generously buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; dot with butter and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(spicy)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°, and bake 45 minutes.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Trim skin and pink flesh; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Dissolve salt in 1 quart water.
Add rind; add more water to cover rind if needed.
Let stand 6 hours.
Drain, rinse and cover with water. Cook, covered, for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Combine spices and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add rind; simmer about 1 hour or until rind is translucent.
Remove spice bag.
Pack hot into sterilized jars.
Screw cover tight.
Substitute cucumbers for watermelon.
It's good also.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook ingredients for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dissolve one 3 ounce package of gelatin (any flavor) in hot rhubarb.
Cool.
Store in freezer.

title: cranberry-apple crunch
directions: Place apples and cranberries in buttered dish.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix the flour, brown sugar, nuts and oats. Sprinkle dry mixture over apple cranberry mixture.
Melt butter and pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fiesta pork burritos
directions: Cut boneless loin into strips.
Stir-fry with vegetable oil and onion.
Stir in can of corn.
Toss with taco seasoning.
Roll up portions in 4 warmed tortillas and serve with salsa, rice and beans.
Serves 4.

title: pizza style macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain off any grease. Mix all the rest of the ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Very good.

title: mexican meat mix chimichangas
directions: Cook meat, then cool and shred.
Set aside.
Melt shortening in large skillet; add onions and green chilies.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add green chili salsa, garlic powder, flour, salt and cumin.
Cook 1 minute over medium-low heat; stir in meat juices. Add shredded meat.
Cook 5 minutes until thick.
Put in tortilla shells and fry at 365° until golden brown or serve burrito style. Optional:
Smother tortilla with meat sauce.
Dab sour cream on top and side with shredded lettuce.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and cover saucepan.
Let it stand, covered for about 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings, 3.5 point per serving.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Combine molasses and sugar; mix well. Add next 9 ingredients in order listed, mixing well. Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Do not remove from pan; let cool completely, then spread top of gingerbread with Lemon-Cream Cheese Frosting. Cut into squares and garnish with lemon twists. Yield: 15 to 18 servings.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat milk and sugar to rolling boil, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add chocolate, stirring until melted. Beat over heat until smooth.
(If sauce has a slightly curdled appearance, beat vigorously until creamy smooth.)
Remove from heat; blend in butter, vanilla and salt.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and pound into meat.
Brown meat on both sides in hot shortening.
Top with onion and cut up tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add green peppers and cook 15 minutes more.
Skim off excess fat and thicken juices if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Pour over nuts and dates.
Mix.
Melt butter. Cool. Beat egg yolks and mix with butter.
Pour over flour and nut mixture.
Mix well. Beat egg whites. Fold in mixture gently.
Pour in tube pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and cook at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn a la rondini
directions: Dissolve cheese and butter in boiler;
Add milk, flour and salt.
Mix well.

title: herbed grill vegetables
directions: In a medium bowl, toss the red pepper, zucchini and squash with thyme, oregano and black pepper.
Drizzle 1 teaspoon of oil over vegetables and toss well.
Spread vegetables in a single layer on rack.
Cook vegetables 8 inches from heat until golden brown on both sides (3 to 4 minutes each side).
Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: For this cake, use a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, cornstarch, salt and Karo.
Cook until clear.
Remove from stove and add dry strawberry gelatin.
Mix very well.
Cool and pour over fresh strawberries.
Pour into a cool pie shell.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries and place in cooled pie shell; set aside. Combine in saucepan the water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Continue to cook over low heat for 2 minutes longer or until mixture is clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Pour while hot evenly over strawberries.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: green pepper meat loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs and milk; add eggs, salt, pepper, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, onion and green pepper; mix well.
Add ground beef and mix thoroughly.
Pack into greased loaf pan.
Bake in
moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cool five sherbet
directions: Mix juices and sugar.
Add fruits, milk and cream.
Freeze. When firm, beat until mushy.
Refreeze.

title: matthew's macaroni and cheese
directions: First I would take the noodles out.
Then put it in the microwave.
The cheese will melt down.
Cook it on 12 degrees, like 6 minutes.
If it's hot, I'll put it in the refrigerator to let it cool down for a little bit.
I want it to be cheesy shells. Then I'll take it out of the refrigerator.
Then I'll eat it.
I drink bubbly juice with.
I like little hamburger balls with it. Sometimes I eat it with a stack of noodles and one big, round hamburger ball.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix spice in water and pour over meat.
Cook in covered pot for 3 hours.
Cool.
When chilled, slice; then heat in broth.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook onion and pepper until transparent.
Add other ingredients.
Stuff into peppers and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Beat together oleo, sugar and honey.
Add beaten egg yolks (6 yolks beaten until light).
Add sifted mixture of flour, baking powder, spices (cinnamon, nutmeg, etc.) and salt, plus 1/2 cup milk.
Add 1 cup chopped figs or dates, 1 cup nuts (chopped) and 1 cup chopped raisins.
Fold in 6 egg whites (beaten stiff).
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Dot bottom of pan with margarine.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over butter.
Spoon the fruit on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili cheese puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well.
Stir in ingredients in order they are listed.
Pour into a greased 8-inch baking dish or glass pie pan.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Top with salsa.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together except soda.
Cream the sugar, shortening and oleo.
Add soda to sour milk.
Add eggs, then alternating adding dry ingredients and milk.
Bake at 400°.
Use rounded teaspoons for each cookie.
Press bottom of flat tumbler dampened and covered with sugar lightly on each cookie.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add 1/2 can of beer.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Drop fish into batter, rolling to make sure they are covered. Drop into deep fryer.
Allow to cook until golden brown. The results will be a crisp, flaky, tasty batter that accents the taste of the fish.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze well.
Mix in stuffing mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form balls the size of large marbles. Freeze on cookie sheet.
Bake, frozen, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Beat egg with milk then add oil. Add liquids all at once with dry ingredients and beat until smooth. If using berries, stir in gently. Bake on hot griddle until bubbles appear, turn and lightly brown other side.

title: pralines
directions: Heat sugar, syrup, water and pecans in a heavy pan until sugar is dissolved. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally, until it reaches the soft-ball stage (240°). Remove pan from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: m&m's fudge jumbles
directions: Heat oven to 370°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Stir together brownie mix (dry), flour, oil, water and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in candies.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls 3 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or just until set and tops are dry.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Makes about 15 large cookies.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients by hand. Add eggs and milk. Fold in fruit cocktail and oil. Bake as needed in well greased or paper-lined muffin tin. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let batter stand at least 24 hours before baking first batch. Batter may be refrigerated up to 6 weeks.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well. Add salt, melted butter and sugar.
Beat well. Add milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake 7 minutes at 425°, then bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except flour) and beat well.
Add flour and mix with spoon.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cover apricots with water and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain and cut up.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pack into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain pork and beans.
Remove bacon fat.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sauce through beans.
Place bacon on top and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; mix into the sugar and shortening mixture. Add coconut and flavor.
Roll dough into small balls.
Dip top into water, then into sugar.
Place on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes, or until brown. Makes 4 dozen.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan beat egg yolks and milk.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir into milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-high heat until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Beat in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Turn into pie shell. Beat egg whites and place on pie.
Sprinkle coconut over meringue.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: mustard ring salad
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler.
In another dish, mix thoroughly sugar and gelatin.
Stir in mustard, turmeric and salt. Add water and vinegar to eggs; stir in sugar mixture.
Cook over boiling water until thick, stirring eggs constantly.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart mold or individual molds. Center may be filled with black olives or cole slaw.
Great with ham.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Soak raisins in orange juice; set aside.
Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs.
Stir in carrots.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda, then all spices and salt.
Add 1/2 of the flour mixture to carrot mixture.
Stir in raisins, then remaining flour and mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 5-cup mold. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix together, cover and cook for 5 to 6 hours at 275° in oven.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries, berry juice and drained pineapple.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 8 x 10-inch square pan and let set until gelled.
Spread with sour cream and add remaining gelatin mixture.
Gel until firm.

title: sweet corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease the muffin tin.
In large bowl, combine corn meal, flour, baking soda, salt, and sugar. Stir to mix.
In medium bowl, beat together the butter, sour cream, and eggs.
Add to the dry ingredients and stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake for about 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and using the back of a teaspoon, make an indentation in the center of each muffin.
Put about 1/2 teaspoon of the preserves into the hole.
Return to oven and continue baking for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove the muffins from the pan and cool slightly on a rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg. Stir into beaten eggs and milk. Add melted butter and stir thoroughly. Pour into pastry shells and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done (about 30 to 35 minutes). Makes 2 pies.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain fat.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon together. Press half of crumbs in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb or apples. Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla. Cook until thick.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: helen's shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, celery, peppers and garlic in butter until almost tender.
Do not brown.
Add tomato sauce, paste, puree, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Simmer until flavors blend.
Add shrimp which are well drained.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
You may add cooked rice to Creole or serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar and beaten eggs; mix well.
Mash bananas and rub through sieve.
Add milk.
Add nuts to sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Fold into creamed mixture gradually.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab meat cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into patties and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wylene's wild rice baron
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Drain rice, if necessary. Layer rice, then sauteed vegetables and cover with cheese in a
1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour half and half over the top.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes and then uncovered for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
This is very good with Sherried Beef.

title: chicken pudding
directions: Combine 1/3 cup flour with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Coat chicken in mixture.
Cook chicken in moderately hot oil for 4 minutes on each side.
Add stock and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Combine rice, soups and water in casserole dish.
Roll chicken in margarine and sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika. Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375 degrees or 2 hours at 300 degrees.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Combine melted butter, onion, salt, cottage cheese, broccoli and beaten eggs, blending well.
Sour cream may be substituted for cottage cheese.
Stir in muffin mix. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fantastic meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, chopped onion, bread crumbs, salt and pepper together.

Shape into loaf and bake in pan until just about done. Sprinkle cheese over loaf and pour mushroom soup over top. Continue to bake at 350° until meat is done and cheese is melted, approximately 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: frozen daiquiri slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Spoon into glasses and add 7-UP.

title: cabbage and sausage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, season and drain. Cook sausage and drain.
Mix cabbage, sausage, Ro-Tel and soup. Serve while hot.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Beat egg yolks and add to chocolate.
Beat egg whites and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Add to chocolate mixture, then add nuts, vanilla, whipped cream and salt. Break cake into chunks and make layers of cake and chocolate mixture in a pan until both are used up.
Freeze overnight.

title: six minute fudge
directions: In large bowl, place nuts, chocolate chips, butter and vanilla over medium heat. Cook sugar and milk until it comes to a boil; stir constantly and boil for 6 minutes. Pour over chips and nut mixture. Stir until chips melt and candy is smooth. Pour in buttered pans.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and pale yellow. Gradually beat in sugar.
Mix flour with baking powder, salt and lemon rind.
Set aside.
Mix vanilla and heavy cream.

Alternately add flour and cream to eggs, beginning and ending with flour. Pour the batter into a greased and floured 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour 40 minutes or until it feels firm to the touch and is dry when tested in center with toothpick.
Stir lemon juice and sugar until dissolved.
Spoon mixture evenly on top of warm cake.
Let it soak in.
Cool cake in its pan on rack or take up onto plate.

title: pasta in brodo de pollo(italian chicken soup with spaghetti)
directions: Simmer all ingredients in a 10-quart covered pan until tender. Remove chicken.
Leave cover off and boil the stock until reduced to half.
Strain; let stand until fat rises to top.
Skim off most of the fat.
Bone chicken.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream first six ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the top with the nuts and chips.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown sausage and cook carrots with caraway seed in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until cabbage is tender, about 1/2 hour, stirring often.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Beat margarine in a large bowl with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar and beat until well combined.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add the flour mixture to the beaten mixture.
Beat at low speed just until combined.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate pieces and pecans.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate pieces left and shortening in a small pan and heat over low heat.
Drizzle over bars.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Boil 1 cup diced celery in salt water until tender.
Set aside 1/2 cup noodles.
In casserole, combine rest of noodles with other ingredients including celery.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup noodles over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: nacho platter
directions: Layer the ingredients on a platter.

title: sandy freire's cherry surprise
directions: Spread cherries in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Top with almonds.
Pour butter evenly over all.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven, until nuts are brown.

title: yankee salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and fold in Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: biscuits
directions: Work flour, sugar, baking powder and margarine together until like corn meal.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Mix with dry ingredients until gooey.
Turn dough out onto a floured board; press with hands to about 1/2-inch and cut out with a cutter or glass.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In mixing bowl, combine softened cream cheese and extract. Gradually beat in powdered sugar with electric mixer until smooth. Knead in the last of powdered sugar by hand.
Knead in food coloring until evenly distributed.
Form mixture into 3/4-inch balls; place on waxed paper.
Flatten each with the tines of a fork.
Let dry overnight.
Makes 4 dozen patties.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger until no longer pink. Boil noodles according to package directions. In a mixing bowl, combine salt, pepper, onions and eggs.
In baking pan, layer noodles and hamburger filling. Spread cheeses over mixture. Continue layers until ingredients are gone.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Put bananas and milk in blender and whip.
When blended, add vanilla ice cream and lightly blend.
Makes 2 servings.
For 4 people, double ingredients.
Refreshing and filling treat!

title: garlic-cheesy potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, skin side down, in baking dish.
Mix oil, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic, paprika and pepper together. Spoon this over the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: bran muffins\(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Spoon batter into muffin pan sprayed with no stick cooking spray.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12 servings.
Serve warm.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat, sausage and onion together.
Melt cheese and add all ingredients to meat.
Serve warm.

title: mixed veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in ungreased casserole. Melt 1/2 stick butter and crush 1/2 stack of crackers and spread on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly and browned, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift the cake flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Cream butter and Crisco, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix in vanilla and part of milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with remaining milk.
Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean, about 1 1/4 hours.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Add milk, lemon juice, rind, flour and melted butter. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish (greased).
Set in shallow pan of water and bake at 350° until firm and golden brown (about 35 to 40 minutes).
This dessert has a firm cake on top with a soft pudding underneath.
Best when completely cool.
This recipe is 150 years old!

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix the soup and sour cream together with chicken. Top with poppy seed and crackers, then pour melted butter over crackers and mix. Top chicken. Bake at 350° until brown and warmed through.

title: mom's thumb cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and egg yolk; knead in flour. Chill for at least 2 hours.
Take 1 teaspoon of mixture and roll into a ball.
Press center with thumb and fill with thick preserves of your choice (strawberry, apricot, etc.).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken & spinach quiche
directions: Pierce and bake pie shell at 375 degree for 10 minutes. Mix, chicken, cheese, spinach, and onion. Spoon into baked shell.

title: easy hamburger with mushroom gravy
directions: Pat out hamburger and cook well.
Drain.
Add soup and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon-garlic shrimp kabobs
directions: *Or 4 chicken thighs, skinned and cut into strips.

title: charlie's vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat.
Combine all ingredients in large soup pot and simmer covered for 2 hours.

title: oil pan pot roast
directions: In a large, heavy kettle, brown beef in its own fat.
Pour off fat.
Add sliced onion, cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour. Put meat in shallow pan to cool.
Cut into attractive serving-size slices.
Return to kettle and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 2 hours, or until tender.
Turn slices once.
Add potatoes during the last 45 minutes of cooking.
Remove meat and potatoes to hot platter.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time, on low speed.
Add extract.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° preheated oven.

title: cocoa fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan; set aside. Sift flour, cocoa, sugar, salt and soda together in large bowl. Add vinegar, vanilla, water and oil.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in the center.
Allow to cool.
Ice in the pan with cocoa frosting.
Makes 24 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve jello and Kool-Aid in hot water.
Add a little water to sugar in a saucepan and dissolve thoroughly.
Mix all together and add pineapple juice in a gallon plastic jug and fill with water and freeze.
Thaw when ready to use and add ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: lazy man's pierogi
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Save bacon fat and fry the onions until clear.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Combine bacon, sausage, onion, mushrooms and sauerkraut with undiluted mushroom soup.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Combine all ingredients, including caraway seed and salt and pepper, in large casserole.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
