Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: monterey spinach soup
directions: Put all together in a saucepan, heat and serve.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper. Coat with flour.
Brown on all sides in oil. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until rice is done and chicken is tender.

title: sweet and sour chicken livers
directions: Cut livers in half and pat dry with paper towels.
Shake in a plastic bag with cornstarch.
In a 12-inch skillet, heat oil over high heat until hot.
Add red pepper and cook, stirring 1 minute. Add livers and cook, stirring often, until brown outside but still rosy inside, about 3 minutes.
Add garlic and ginger and reduce heat to medium.
Mix together soy sauce, sugar, sherry and vinegar.
Add to skillet; cover and cook 8 minutes.
Stir in frozen pasta salad and drained pineapple chunks.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with scallions.

title: franks and stuffin' casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, oregano and tomato juice; stir well.
Slice the franks and cut up five slices of the cheese.
Add to the first mixture and pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and brown under broiler.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Mix water, oil and Tabasco.

Roll potatoes in this mixture. Mix cheese and Shake'n Bake, then roll potatoes in this mixture. Bake in tinfoil on a baking sheet for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°. May be uncovered last few minutes for baking time for crispness.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with graham crackers (do not crush).
Combine vanilla pudding and milk as directed on box of pudding.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Spread half of pudding mixture on top of crackers.
Repeat with another layer of graham crackers and pudding.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Spread chocolate frosting over top.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: pistachio salad 1
directions: Mix and freeze.
Serve as a salad or as a dessert in a graham cracker crust.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Cook sugar and water until it will spin a thread.
Do not stir.
Add slowly to stiffly beaten egg whites. Beat until of consistency to spread on outside of cake.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices, salt and pumpkin.
Stir in eggs.
Add milk.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drizzle oil over.
Sprinkle with garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper; toss gently to coat.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender when pierced with a fork. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal chewies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken filled dumplings
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Combine next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Roll 10 biscuits (Grands) into larger circle.
Place a 1/4 cup chicken in center of biscuits. Wrap dough around and seal edges.
Put into liquid.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.

title: arctic orange pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese and orange juice concentrate until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Cover and freeze for (4) hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with oranges. Yield:
8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil in large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Add eggs.
Add orange juice and pumpkin.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour batter evenly into pans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel, slice or cube potatoes.
Cover with water and cook 20 or 30 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make a white sauce by melting margarine and slowly mixing in flour and salt and cooking over low heat, stirring constantly.
Slowly add milk and onion soup and stir until sauce is lump free.
Pour over potatoes.
Let simmer until soup tastes like you want it.
If thicker than you like it, add a little more milk.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Spread rhubarb in pie shell.
Beat eggs, sugar, cornstarch, vanilla and salt.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 425°
for 5 minutes.
Cut heat down to 325°
and bake another 30 minutes, or until pie is set.

title: "lite" apple oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put batter in muffin cups in muffin pan.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: party egg dip
directions: Grate eggs fine; add remaining ingredients.
Blend well. Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8-inch pan.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Place ground beef in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown. Drain, crumble and set aside. Add all ingredients (except noodles) to browned ground meat and simmer for 1 hour, then add noodles.

title: low-fat easy black forest cake
directions: Bake cake mix by directions on box in sheet cake pan.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour pie filling over cake.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over cherries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and butter; beat with mixer.
Stir in pecans.
Soften chocolate morsels in microwave; add.
Add vanilla; mix all well.
Pour into shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Whip the cream and add 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon bourbon.

title: carrot pineapple salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved; let cool.
Stir in carrots and pineapple.
Put in any oblong or round container.
Put in refrigerator.
Let set until firm, overnight is best.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla. Combine oats, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Stir in butterscotch and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are lightly browned. Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: sweet fruit dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add onion.
Add oil, a small amount at a time, alternately with vinegar, the last addition being vinegar. Beat with a fork or a whisk.
If mixture seems to separate, use rotary or electric beater until blended.
This makes 1 1/2 cups and is delicious on fresh fruit salad.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together nutmeg, sugar, eggs, cinnamon, oil and salt.
Add pumpkin, flour, water and baking soda.
Grease and flour three (1-pound) coffee cans. Pour mixture into cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Can be frozen.

title: tandy cake
directions: Cream eggs, 2 tablespoons oil, vanilla and sugar.
Alternately flour.
Beat well.
Pour into cookie sheet with sides and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
After removing from oven, spread peanut butter and place in fridge until cool.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and oleo.
Melt oleo and add corn flakes.
Sprinkle on casserole and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into 8 x 8-inch or 6 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt butter and sugar in saucepan at low heat.
Remove, add other ingredients in order.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares while hot.

title: layered jar cookies
directions: When ready to make, add margarine, corn syrup or honey, egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream the butter, gradually adding sugar. Add vanilla.
Cream together. Gradually add flour, then nuts. Chill for awhile so it will shape good.
Shape in crescents (half moons). Bake at 350° about 12 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar. Can shape in balls if you like.
I makes these every year at Christmas.

title: beef roast with veggies(crock-pot)
directions: Put all in crock-pot.
Cover with soup and 1/2 cup water. Cook on low all day or 5 hours on high.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare sliced peaches and mix with 1 cup sugar.
Set oven at 350°.
Put half stick of butter in a very deep baking dish.
Set in oven to melt.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Add Hidden Valley dry mix to prepared mashed potatoes.
Stir well.
Add butter or margarine to taste.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients three times.
Add this and milk alternately.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
(I use Red Band plain flour.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in large bowl sugar, oil, egg and flour.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured rectangular cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put zucchini in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle onion and carrot on top.
Spread soup and sour cream mixture over top. Cover with bread crumbs.
Drizzle butter over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked chicken with mushrooms
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Test with a fork to see if chicken is done.

title: chocolate peanut cups
directions: Cut cookie dough into 3/4-inch slices.
Cut each slice into quarters.
Roll quarters into balls.
Place in ungreased miniature muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown. Remove wrappers from candies.
Press into hot cookies.
Loosen edges with knife.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Remove from muffin cups.

title: baked onions
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch buttered casserole, place alternate layers of thinly sliced onions, crushed potato chips and grated cheese.
Combine mushroom soup with milk and pour over top of the onion mixture.
Sprinkle pepper over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: country ham with red-eye gravy
directions: Trim fat off ham.
Saute fat in a heavy skillet until enough fat is rendered to coat bottom of skillet.
Add ham.
Cook, turning several times until heated through.
Remove ham and keep warm.
Stir brown sugar into drippings.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts.
Add coffee or water. Stir 5 minutes or until mixture is a rich red-brown color.
Spoon gravy onto a warm serving platter and top with ham slices.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Can put in round loaf of rye bread or use with chips, vegetables, etc.

title: cream of broccoli-vegetable soup
directions: Combine celery, onion, frozen broccoli and chicken broth in a medium-sized saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place half the soup mixture and half of the cottage cheese in blender container. Cover.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a 3-quart saucepan.
Repeat with remaining vegetables and cottage cheese.
Stir in milk, cooked vegetables, salt and pepper.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add oil and mix next four ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with electric blender for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Grind orange, peel and all.
Put cranberries, orange, grapes and nuts in a bowl.
Add drained, crushed pineapple.
Boil 2 cups water and 2 cups sugar.
Add to lemon jello and pour over fruits.
Chill.
It does not set.

title: rainbow slices
directions: Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Blend in egg and powdered sugar.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts until coated.
On waxed paper, shape coconut in a 16 x 8-inch rectangle. Roll log in coconut, coating completely.
Chill several hours (for best results, chill overnight).
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Bring milk and cornstarch to boil.
Cook until thick.
Then cover and cool in refrigerator.
Beat together butter, shortening and sugar for about 10 minutes.
Add cooled cornstarch with vanilla.
Beat on high until creamy, about 10 minutes.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, oil and vanilla. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased 9X13 pan. Combine pecans, sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over batter. Cut through with a knife to swirl. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. In a small bowl combine powdered sugar and orange juice until smooth. Drizzle over warm coffeecake.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Preheat grill to high.
Soak mesquite for 1 hour in water to cover.
Drain and place in an aluminum pan.
Place pan on hot coals in a covered grill.
Place tomatoes, peppers and onions in aluminum or metal pans placed on a rack in the grill.
Close grill cover and smoke for 20 minutes.
Remove from grill and cool.
Peel onions.
Put tomatoes, peppers and onions in a large saucepan. Add remaining ingredients and simmer over medium heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Baste on your favorite meat, fish or poultry.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: shortbread
directions: Add dry ingredients and beat with mixer.
Press in 8-inch cake pan.
Top with sugar.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm in slices.

title: ayres chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery in bowl. Mix together remaining ingredients and combine with chicken. Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together well in bowl.
Drop by small balls on cookie sheet.
Dip fork in sugar to press each cookie down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and flour; mix well. Add vanilla; mix.
Stir in blueberries very gently.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken with bread crumbs
directions: Rinse chicken breasts.
Place chicken and Italian dressing in one baggie.
Let marinate in refrigerator.
Place bread crumbs, garlic, salt and pepper in baggie.
Mix.
Drop chicken pieces in bag of crumbs and coat completely.
Place on baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add soup, water, seasonings, corn and green pepper; mixing well.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Fill well-greased casserole 3/4 full, leaving room for topping.
Mix together cornmeal, flour, sugar, buttermilk, egg and fat.
Pour on top of casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Topping will disappear into beef mixture and rise during baking.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover meat; add salt, pepper and bay leaves.
Let it come to a boil; turn heat down and add celery, onion, carrots and cabbage. Simmer 2 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon cube; simmer another 1/2 hour.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: You will need 1 large sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: amy's play dough
directions: Mix water and salt together.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
One may want to divide the dough to make different colors.
Let dough cool and place in an airtight container.

title: sausage gravy
directions: In a large skillet, crumble sausage and cook until done. Sprinkle the flour over the cooked sausage and let it brown. Stir in the milk and water. Cook on low until you reach desired thickness. Serve with biscuits.

title: virginia's easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; simmer 10 minutes.
In a bowl, stir together Ricotta, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3 uncooked pasta pieces lengthwise over sauce; cover with 1 cup of sauce.
Spread 1/2 cheese filling over sauce. Repeat layer of lasagne, sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagne and remaining sauce; sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 15 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate flake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter and flour 8 1/2-inch spring-form cake pan.
Place sugar in stainless steel bowl; set over saucepan half filled with hot water.
Add eggs.
Over low heat with water simmering whisk for 4 to 5 minutes.
Use electric hand mixer if desired.
Mixture should become quite thick and expand in volume.
When cream forms ribbons, transfer bowl to counter.
Sift 1 cup of flour over bowl; fold in using spatula until all traces are gone.
Sift in rest of flour and fold using spatula.
Gradually add butter while folding.
All traces of butter must be incorporated.
Pour batter into cake pan and bake in middle of oven 35 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then unmold and finish cooling on wire rack.
When cool, slice off layer, sprinkle Tia Maria over bottom layer and cover with pastry cream.
Replace top layer, sprinkle with more liqueur and ice outside of cake with remaining cream.
Top with chocolate flakes; chill for two hours.

title: cheesy cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender, not done.
Drain cabbage and spread in large casserole.
Melt soup, milk, Cheez Whiz, margarine, salt and pepper together.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan with vegetable oil spray.
Simmer pineapple juice until it's reduced to 3/4 cup.
Mix applesauce and egg whites in a large bowl.
Stir in lemon rind, Jell-O and cake mix.
Slowly add pineapple juice; beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and powdered sugar and pour over hot cake.

title: lo-cal all occasion cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well, then add remaining ingredients to same bowl.
Begin by buttering a 7 x 11-inch baking pan thoroughly.
Do not use another size pan.
Drizzle pan bottom with liquid honey to cover.
Top honey with whatever you want on top of cake, a cup of chopped nuts or coconut or a cup of sweet pineapple, plums or berries.
Stir batter about 75 strokes, then pour it over topping.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes in pan, then invert and serve.

title: bisquick bars
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar and eggs with mixer.
Add pecans and coconut and stir with spoon.
Spread into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; do not overcook.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a Bundt pan or other fluted cake pan well and coat with some of the chopped nuts.
Break frozen rolls apart and arrange 12 over the nuts.
Sprinkle half the dry pudding mix on top, then sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.

Arrange remaining 12 rolls in the pan and sprinkle with remaining pudding mix and cinnamon. Scatter remaining nuts on top. Bring butter and brown sugar to a rolling boil in saucepan and pour over rolls.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, salt and syrup in a deep bowl with a handle; cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 3 minutes longer. Add butter and vanilla; cook 2 minutes.
Add soda; stir.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool; then break into small portions.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Do not brown meat first.)

title: chocolate and peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, baking cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan. Bring just to the boiling point over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined trays.
Cool until firm. Yield:
32 servings.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken and enough water to cover in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth for other uses.
Let chicken cool.
Skin, bone and cut into bite-size pieces, set aside. Place broccoli in a lightly greased 11X7X1 1/2-inch baking dish. Top with chicken.
Combine soup and next 3 ingredients, pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and stuffing mix.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: jiffy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add other ingredients, except sour cream. Cook with lid for 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and reheat 2 or 3 minutes, until hot.

title: spinach frittata *
directions: Wilt spinach with 2 tablespoons oil.
Drain.
In large bowl, beat eggs lightly.
Add remaining ingredients, except oil.
Heat oil in heat bottomed and broiler proof skillet.
Pour in mixture; cook over gentle heat until bottom sets.
Place in broiler until lightly browned and set.
Turn out onto platter.
Cut like a cake. Eat hot or cold.
Yields 4 to 6 good slices.

title: green chile stew
directions: Brown beef or pork and potatoes together. Stir constantly to prevent sticking. Drain excess fat. Add green chili, tomatoes, salts and water. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crunchy potato wedges
directions: Combine seasonings in a shallow dish.
Place butter in glass mixing bowl; microwave one minute until melted.
Cut potatoes in half, lengthwise into three wedges.
Dip in butter and then in cheese mixture.
Place cut-side up in baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High power for 10-12 minutes or until tender.

title: ann waldrop's easy broccoli casserole
directions: Oil a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in the casserole, except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Reheats well.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Cover foil with rows of saltine crackers.
Cook together butter and white sugar for 3 minutes or until foamy.
Pour over crackers and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely; it will burn easily.
Melt in microwave 1 bag of milk chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons Crisco.
Mix in 1 cup chopped nuts and spread with spoon over baked mixture.
Cool in refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Save small amount of Cool Whip to use for topping.
Cream the cream cheese good and then add sugar.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla, then add Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust.
In center of pie, place the cherry pie filling.
Place small teaspoonful of Cool Whip around edge of pie.
For variety, blueberry pie filling and fresh strawberries in the gel are really good.
Can be eaten immediately or kept several days in refrigerator.

title: 5 bean dinner
directions: Brown sausage and put all in a crock-pot and cook at least 4 to 5 hours.
Great dish for a barbecue.

title: grapefruit punch
directions: Combine sugar, water, cloves and allspice.
Heat to boiling and simmer 5 minutes.
Strain into pitcher and cool.
Stir in juice, ginger ale and food coloring.
Pour over ice cubes and garnish with lemon and cherries.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add beaten egg and mix very well.
Mix and sift flour and soda together, adding sour cream alternately with flour. Add flavoring last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese, then add eggs and 2 tablespoons milk to this and beat.
Put the custard mixture over the crumbs in the pan and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Cool.
Then spread blueberry pie filling over top of custard.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package, adding 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons milk.
Spread over top of blueberries and sprinkle with the 1/2 cup of crumb mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, water, onion and celery in a pan, cover and cook 20 minutes on medium heat.
Add potatoes and frozen vegetables.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese.
Heat on low until cheese melts, stirring frequently.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Gradually add sugar, crackers, baking powder, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Thoroughly grease 8-inch
pie
tin.
Spread
mixture in pie tin.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook the Rice-A-Roni as directed on package.
Cool completely. Add remaining ingredients to rice mixture.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water until soft.
Set aside.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Brown bread cubes in butter.
(This may be done ahead of time.) Mix well beaten eggs, can of pineapple, flour and sugar.
Place in buttered casserole.
Toss bread cubes in lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.
Delicious with vanilla ice cream

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add butter, sugar, oats, cinnamon, salt and syrup.
Mix well.
Fold in oats and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut roll
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch, cream, butter and salt to soft ball stage.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy; add raisins, nuts, coconut and flavoring.
Continue beating until mixture can be handled.
Turn onto board dusted with powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth and creamy.
Shape into a roll.
Sprinkle with additional toasted coconut.

title: chinese beef and peppers
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic in oil until meat is browned.
Add ginger, thinly sliced peppers, bouillon and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: trudy's hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large container and mix well.

title: perfect divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff
in large glass bowl.
Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage.
Pour 1/3 (you can guess at this) of mixture over egg whites, beating well.
Cook rest of mixture to hard ball stage.
Pour 1/2 of this over egg whites, beating well.
Cook remaining syrup to hard crack stage (this will cook quickly).
Beat into other mixture until it starts to lose its gloss.
Add vanilla, then nuts or fruit.
Pour into well-greased pans.
This makes a lot but always turns out perfect. Worth the extra trouble.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan with cooking spray. In a large bowl, with electric mixer, cream the margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In separate medium bowl, combine dry ingredients and stir well. Add dry mixture to moist batter and mix on low speed while adding milk. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Let cake cool 10 minutes in pan, then remove cake and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Make cornbread and break up.
Let dry 1 day.
Remove giblets from turkey in 1-quart of water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add heated milk slowly and cook in a double boiler until thickened.
Add egg yolks and butter.
Reheat.
Add flavoring and cool.
Beat egg whites.
Fill crust with filling.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: salmon patties
directions: Pour undrained salmon into bowl, removing bones.
Mix in egg. Add onion, salt, milk, flour, stirring well.
Shape mixture into patties.
Fry in hot oil in skillet for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until browned; drain.
Serve with potato salad.
May top the patties with chili powder gravy.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt margarine in medium-size saucepan. Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion. Stir in sour cream. Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring occasionally. Fold in green beans. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray. Combine Kellogg's cornflake crumbs with 1 tablespoon margarine and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar. Add flour and butter and mix well. Add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Let stand for 2 hours before cutting.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices and halve these.
Cut tomatoes in pieces.
Place with zucchini in 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, onions, salt and pepper. Sprinkle over vegetables.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake for 45 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Cook chicken, then mix all ingredients together and add noodles last.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly in a 350° oven.

title: blushing apples
directions: In large saucepan, dissolve sugar and red hots in water; bring to boil.
Simmer apples in this mixture until apples are cooked, turning so all slices are cooked.
Nice meat accompaniment. Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange salad dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour and sugar. Add buttermilk and chopped onion. Blend all together. Drop by spoonfuls into hot Crisco oil. Brown lightly until done. When both sides are browned evenly, take up and drain on a paper towel.

title: russian tea #2
directions: Boil together water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves and boil 10 minutes. Add orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice and tea. Remove spices; bring to boil again. Serve hot or cold. Makes 2 gallons.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Remove from fire.
Put tea and cloves together in a bag.
Drop into mixture and let stay until desired strength.
Take out bag and add lemon juice.

title: cantaloupe soup
directions: Combine orange juice, wine, honey, orange peel and cinnamon stick; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in lemon juice and whisk into simmering liquid.
Keep simmering and whisk until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and remove cinnamon stick.
Chill until cold.
Puree cantaloupe with cream (do in batches) and stir puree into cold juice mixture. Chill until serving time.
Can be frozen.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Brown beef and season.
Layer half the chilies in a large casserole dish.
Layer beef and cheese.
Layer remaining chilies. Beat egg whites until stiff.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and salt and pepper.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour over chilies.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups strawberries in pie shell.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and water; cook until thick.
Add crushed strawberries.
Pour over strawberries in crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: shake it up party mix
directions: Melt margarine.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well.
Pour cereal, nuts and pretzels into Glad-Lock zipper bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside bag. Seal.
Shake well.
Pour contents into microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Stop to stir every minute.

title: miracle pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine (it is important to use whipped margarine).
Add sugar and cream together again.
Add 1/2 flour and 1/2 of the milk; blend.
Add eggs one at a time with the remaining milk and flour.
Add flavoring.

title: caramel french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Pour syrup into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Arrange bread slices over syrup.

title: lucille's pineapple timbale
directions: Add pineapple, bread and sugar together. Let stand a few hours. Pour half of butter on 8 x 8 pan.
Add pineapple mixture and then rest of butter on top. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Double recipe for 9 x 13 pan. Serves 6 to 8 (12 to 16). I haven't tried to freeze or do ahead. Must partially do ahead.

title: new england cake icing
directions: Blend sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks. Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat smooth.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Boil the soup, rice and water for 7 minutes; do not drain. In skillet, cook sausage, onion, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Pour meat mixture into rice mixture; stir well.
Put in a casserole dish (12 x 8-inch).
Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: healthy chili
directions: Saute ground turkey in a large Dutch oven until no longer pink.
Add the vegetables and garlic.
Cook until crisp-tender. Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Garnish with 1 tablespoon grated low-fat Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Serve with crusty bread or tortillas. (Also good served over a baked potato.) Serves 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, adding salt and pepper to taste. Add noodles, then hot water.
Mix cinnamon to onion soup mix and add to ground beef and noodles.
Add mushrooms.
When noodles are almost done, add flour to sour cream and add to mixture.
Simmer slowly until noodles are done.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Chill dough for about 2 hours.
Drop dough onto a greased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until nice and golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Cool and serve or store.

title: company potatoes
directions: Heat soup and butter until melted.
Stir in sour cream and pour over potatoes.
Add green onions and stir in cheese.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to heat.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes. Then slice them up. Mix salt, pepper and flour. Coat tomato slices in flour mixture and put in hot oil. Fry until golden brown. Drain.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press into greased pan.
Mix together last 3 ingredients.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If time permits, refrigerate the salsa for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Add corned beef, onion, cheese and soup mixture with milk.
Top with buttered crumbs or chips.
Bake until brown in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar-free applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. Sift together the first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Cream the margarine until fluffy.
Blend in brown Sugar Twin and egg. Alternately add dry ingredients and applesauce; blend well.
Add vanilla, oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon, then flatten.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Whisk first 4 ingredients well (mix strawberries with lettuce and almonds).
Place on 6 plates. Drizzle dressing over lettuce, strawberries and almonds.

title: swiss enchiladas
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine in skillet.
Add chicken and cashews.
Stir in sour cream and 2/3 cup half and half.
Cook mixture until thickened.
Place chicken mixture along center of tortillas.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in buttered baking dish.
Pour remaining half and half over rolls. Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle with sugar; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine dressing ingredients; bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat and pour over vegetables, stirring to cover evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together. Pour over salad mixture.
Toss gently.
Chill.

title: shep's grandmother's "three john" sherbet
directions: Squeeze juice from oranges and lemons.
Mash bananas.
Put all through strainer.
Add water and sugar; stir until dissolved. Freeze until mushy.
Then open and quickly turn in beaten egg whites.
Finish freezing.

title: tyuane torte
directions: Brown, drain and rinse ground beef.
Add tomatoes, onion, diced chilies and taco seasoning mix and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Grease pan and layer half a package of flour tortillas. Add meat mixture and 1 3/4 pounds grated Cheddar cheese.
Top with sour cream, the rest of the flour tortillas and 1/4 pounds grated cheese.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together and fry on hot grill like pancakes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and wash with cold water and drain. Mix other ingredients.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Chill.
Makes a large amount.
Will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: deep dish custard french toast(nest of the moon cafe)
directions: Lightly grease	an
8 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan.
Butter both sides
of
each
of
slices of 1-inch thick Portuguese sweet bread
(Hawaiian bread).
Arrange the bread side by side in the baking pan, then sprinkle the top with cinnamon.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: honey graham bars
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, honey and orange juice; mix well.
Stir in chips.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until springs back, at 325°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with sugar; cut into squares.
Keep at room temperature.

title: chicken with cashews
directions: Cut chicken into strips 1/4 inch thick, 1/2 inch wide and 1 1/2 inches long.
In a wok, over medium heat, saute ginger in oil. Remove ginger.
Cook chicken until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Add vegetables in order given; cook for 2 minutes.
Add chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Cover and steam for 2 minutes. Add vegetable seasoning, tamari and arrowroot that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Stir until mixture is thickened.
Add cashews and stir a couple of times.
Serve immediately over brown rice or fried noodles.
Serves 4.

title: bob's chocolate pie
directions: *Buy 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Use 4 tablespoons for filling and the rest for topping.

title: bean dip
directions: Assemble in layers and enjoy.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream thoroughly 6 tablespoons shortening, 1 cup sugar and 2 eggs in large bowl.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and pinch of salt in small bowl and add alternately with 1/2 cup milk to first batter.
Add grated rind of 1 lemon.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix
cucumbers,
salt
and onion (optional).
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain but don't wash.
Mix vinegar and sugar and pour over cucumbers.
Put into container and freeze.

title: cracker jack
directions: Cook sugar and Karo until light brown.
Add soda and salt (will bubble up).
Pour over popped corn.

title: sugarless chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk until well blended and thickened. Add Cool Whip and blend well. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding mix, layer of graham crackers and layer of pudding mix.

title: mississippi coconut pie
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vinegar, vanilla and salt.
Mix coconut well with all ingredients and turn into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Easy and delicious!

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with egg whites beaten until stiff with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Stir in pineapple, apple, coconut, raisins, carrots and nuts.
Sift in flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Blend well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Better 24 hours after baked.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice 1 package sugar cookie dough and put in 9 x 13-inch pan, closely.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, vanilla and sugar.
Beat until smooth; spread on top of cooled cookie dough.
On top, add in layers:
crushed pineapple, bananas (in single layer), sliced strawberries (as many as you like), sprinkle coconut and handful of pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: ma hoff's meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly (hands work best!). Shape into desired size, golf ball. Brown in oven on greased cookie sheet at 350°. Place meatballs in spaghetti sauce and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla, zucchini, milk and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells.
Bring 4-quarts of water to a rolling boil.
Empty contents of package into boiling water and stir. Return to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, 12 to 14 minutes.
Avoid overcooking.
Drain well and rinse and drain again.
Shrimp will be frozen.
Run cold water over and drain. Mix all other ingredients and chill.
Makes a large amount.

title: easy skillet casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil and onion in large skillet.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
While mixture is simmering, place macaroni in boiling water and cook for 5 minutes.
Add drained macaroni to meat mixture and mix well. Sprinkle top of casserole with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: yankee maple corn muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups.
Thoroughly mix flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Whisk eggs and brown sugar in another bowl until smooth.
Add milk and maple syrup and whisk to mix.
Pour onto
the dry ingredients and add 4 tablespoons of the melted butter.
Fold in with a rubber spatula just until dry ingredients are moistened. Scoop batter into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and firm in center.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes. Brush tops with remaining melted butter.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add milk to corn.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to corn mixture.
Add eggs and butter.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into fat heated to 375°.
When brown, drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: healthful beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour and brown in oil in large container.
Add onion and garlic and cook until softened.
Pour off excess fat. Add celery, spices, water and wine and bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add tomatoes, potatoes and carrots.
Simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until liquid is clear.
Add jello and mix well.
Clean strawberries and add to liquid.
Pour into pie shells and let cool.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Heat soup, using whole milk, as directed on can.
Add bouillon cube and the mushroom mixture.
(Will not taste the same with canned mushrooms.)
Serve with fresh Italian bread, salad and peach halves.

title: ring tum diddy
directions: Cook bacon.
Have pepper and onions cut and ready.
Cook in bacon fat.
Add tomatoes and corn; season to taste.
Just before serving, add the cheese.
Serve on toast or crackers.
I omit toast and crackers and serve as a vegetable.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Boil
first
3	ingredients
until
the hard crack ball stage. Add the cinnamon oil and a few drops of food coloring. Pour
out on foil lined cookie sheet. Cool until hard and then break into pieces.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir margarine into spaghetti.
Stir in eggs and Parmesan cheese. Press spaghetti mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie plate, forming a crust.

title: sue's soft molasses cookies
directions: Add vinegar to milk.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk mixture.
Add egg and molasses; add rest of ingredients.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow graham cracker bars
directions: Put crushed graham crackers in a big bowl and add marshmallows, coconut and chopped nuts.
Heat the sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla over low heat; cool.
Pour over first mixture, then into cake pan and pat down with a spoon.
Put in refrigerator.
Cut into bars. They are better if stored a day before using.

title: chicken and spinach delight
directions: Spread spinach in greased 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top in single layer.
Mix mayonnaise, chicken soup, curry and lemon juice and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vanilla; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to oil mixture alternately with carrots.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for about an hour.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tespoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: olive dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Best if made a day ahead.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.

title: chicken is king
directions: Glaze bell peppers and green onions.
Mix rest of ingredients with chicken juice and milk that have a total volume of 2 1/2 cups.
Heat gently and serve over rice, noodles or toast.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb according to package directions.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup juice and bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool and add 1 cup juice, apples and pecans. Refrigerate.
Serve with dressing.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt oleo and saute onions; do not brown. Add eggs, milk, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole, top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it bubbles in the middle.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Mix liquor, juice, and lemonade. Chill. add carbonated beverages. Add a few drops of red food coloring. Add ice and cut up fruit.

title: tri-color bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine onions, garlic, water, potatoes and carrots; bring to a boil, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add all beans (if

pinto beans are not available, can substitute a can of the other beans called for), oregano, basil, and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors. Makes 12 servings (1 cup each).

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and cook at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: chili
directions: A 1 1/2 to 2-gallon kettle is suggested.
Add equal amount water to tomatoes.
Cook at medium temperature.
Brown beef and onions in shortening; put in kettle.
Add crushed bay leaves and all other seasonings, except coriander.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add coriander 1/2 hour before chili is finished.
Add water as needed.
Mix 3 to 5 heaping tablespoons flour with cold water or tomato juice.
Blend well. Add to chili toward end of cooking time.
Stir thoroughly, when adding flour mixture.
Chili should be made a day in advance of the eating time.

title: ham or pork fried rice
directions: In a large pot, fry rice in butter until brown.
Add all of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drop heat to low.
Cover and simmer approximately 20 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press to bottom of 9 x 13 ungreased cake pan. Scatter chocolate morsels over this mixture. Spread coconut over top of chocolate morsels. Sprinkle nuts on coconut. Drizzle condensed milk over top of nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until lightly brown at edges.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form 2 logs; roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.
Freezes well for later use.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and tomatoes in a large salad bowl. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over the vegetables and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix salt, pepper, chili powder and flour.
Layer potatoes, topped with flour mixture, cheese and butter.
Add hot milk to cover mixture.

title: cherry balls
directions: Blend margarine, sugar, coconut, milk and flavoring well. Wrap 1 teaspoon mixture around each cherry and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Chill one hour.
Cover and store in refrigerator. Yields 18.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Place small amount of oil or shortening in a large skillet. Add sliced zucchini. Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Add browned ground beef and stewed tomatoes. Cook until dry, cover with mozzarella cheese and serve hot.

title: old-fashioned fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples, mash thoroughly.
Add sugar; chill.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and sprinkled with corn meal.
Cover; let rise in warm area for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
Recipe yields 2 loaves, 16 slices per loaf.
To serve, slice and toast.

title: rice dressing
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and brown for last 15 minutes.

title: raisin-coconut bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs & milk, add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Place this in an 8 inch square glass cake dish.
Add vanilla.	Add your bread pieces, coconut, raisins and salt. Do not put too much bread in that it takes up all the milk. Do use your crust. On top add more coconut and sprinkle nutmeg only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no crust egg custard pie
directions: Mix in order listed. Grease baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheesy snackeroos
directions: Prepare according to package directions the cornbread mix. Add 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Place in a well-greased Dutch oven.
Sprinkle over top 3/4 cups nuts, another 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill.
Let stand a while to draw juice from fruits.
Serve well chilled.

title: deviled hamburgers
directions: Have a large steak and pound on both sides with a meat hammer. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.

title: russian easter cheese(cirnaya paska)
directions: Completely drain the whey (liquid) off the cottage cheese with a strainer.
Allow to drain until no liquid is left.
Cream the butter into the sugar and the egg yolks, mix well.
Stir in the vanilla, mix well.
Place a dish towel in a souffle dish and pour in the cheese mixture.
Fold the towel over the mixture and place weigh down with a heavy object.
A small plate that fits inside the dish works well with a large can used for a weight.
Refrigerate for 24 hours and drain off any excess liquid.
Unwrap the cheese and garish with apricots, raisins, nuts or other dried fruit of your choice.
You can slice this into small slices if you desire.

title: spicy beets
directions: Trim the greens from the beets.
Bring 2 inches of water to a boil in a heavy saucepan; add the beets.
Reduce the heat and simmer until the beets are tender, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not let them become mushy.
When tender, drain them and allow to cool. Peel and slice; set aside.

title: taffy candy
directions: Put everything	except	gelatine
and
extract in large pan. Soak gelatine
in
water.
Cook
and stir all time until crackles when tested
in
ice
water.
Take off stove, squeeze all water out of
gelatine and put gelatine in and stir.
Then pour in buttered platters and cool until you can handle.
Pull and put in extract
and
coloring (if wanted).
Cut in chunks with scissors. Makes about 5 pounds.

title: johnny mozetti
directions: Saute ground beef, onions, peppers, olives and celery.
Add mushroom soup, tomato soup and tomato paste.
Season to taste. Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Cut X in top of roast.
Put a clove of garlic in each 4 sections.
Sprinkle with sweet basil and oregano.
Brown in a little oil in a big heavy pan on both sides.
When brown, add onion soup mix, beef bouillon cube, water and beef broth.
Can add a little more water or broth, if needed.
Simmer for 4 hours. Remove, cool and slice thin.
Put back in broth and simmer 1 more hour.
Cool, put in containers and freeze.
Serve on hoagie buns. Can do 2 roasts at one time.

title: cream of potato-vegetable soup
directions: In large pan, place potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Add enough water to cover vegetables and salt to taste.
Cover and boil until tender.
With potato masher, mash the vegetables in the cooked liquid.
Saute 1/4 pound butter and 1/2 cup chopped onion until tender.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and make roux.
Add chicken broth and flour mix to vegetables.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add parsley.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and butter.
Put soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Sift flour, cocoa and spices together. Combine these ingredients to mixture, then add nuts, raisins, jam and pineapple.
Beat well.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Cook at 350°.

title: snow on the mountain
directions: Break angel food cake into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Prepare pudding per instructions on box.
Spread layer of pudding.
Spread layer of Cool Whip.
Top with coconut. Repeat as directed for second layer.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cocoa.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour, about 1/3 cup at a time.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Leave cream cheese out at room temperature until soft.
Mix with mayonnaise, chopped nuts, olives, olive juice and pepper.
It will be quite soft.
Keep in jar and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: busy day meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ketchup in large bowl.
Place in shallow, ungreased baking pan and with wet hands, shape into a loaf.
Spread ketchup over top.
Bake 1 hour or until brown.

title: oven poached halibut
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place fish steaks in rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place dill weed sprigs, lemon slice and peppercorn on each.
Pour wine over fish.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: pumpkin stew
directions: Heat oil and saute onion.
Add meat until brown.
Heat to boiling; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Brush inside of pumpkin with butter, salt and pepper.
Place in Pyrex pan with water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir in corn and marjoram.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces and brown.
Add all ingredients, except rice, and let simmer for 30 minutes on low. Serve with rice.

title: cool and easy dessert
directions: Mix dry pistachio pudding mix with all other ingredients. Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Coat a 12-cup muffin tin with vegetable cooking spray or line with paper muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, whisk the eggs with the buttermilk, honey and oil.
Add the mixture to the dry ingredients.
Add the apple and stir until just combined, but not overmixed.
Fill the prepared muffin cups 3/4 full and bake for about 15 minutes or until golden.
Remove the muffins from the pan. Allow to cool slightly and serve warm.
Makes 18 large muffins.

title: pot roast
directions: Cook roast in covered roaster with onion soup mix, onions and celery at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, then add whole peeled carrots and potatoes.
Cover and cook until tender.
Serve on platter.

title: fry pan cookies
directions: In heavy skillet, mix sugar, dates and eggs.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan, about 5 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes and add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and carefully work in cereal.
Dampen hands in cool water and roll mixture into small balls and roll them in coconut.

title: sugar peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and water over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugar coated and no syrup is left in pan.
Pour and spread over ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals.

title: tea punch
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Boil to dissolve sugar, then add mint and tea.
Set aside to cool.
Add orange juice and the juice of the lemons.
Pour into one gallon jug.
Add water to complete gallon.

title: lorene hooper and mertie ehls' refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add sugar, salt and 1/2 flour.
Beat well, then add egg and shortening.
Beat in well, then add rest of flour.
Blend well and knead.
Put in greased bowl, grease top too. Cover with damp cloth.
Set in refrigerator until morning.
Take out and form into rolls.
Set back in refrigerator.
Two hours before needed, take out and set in warm place, covered.
Bake at 400°.

title: flowerpot dessert(dirt cake)
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, pudding and sugar.
Gradually add milk; set aside to thicken.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour 1/2 in greased pan.
Put cheese on top and add rest of mix.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mincemeat chiffon pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatine on water to soften.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in rum and mincemeat.
Chill in refrigerator or in bowl of ice water, stirring occasionally, until the mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in sugar and salt.
Fold gelatine mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into baked pie shell. Chill until firm.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine the listed ingredients in a large container.
Stir well and pour into quart jars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add gelatin mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts. Chill about 2 hours.

title: savory pork ribs
directions: Parboil ribs in water with salt, garlic powder, sage and onion.
Combine barbecue sauce and honey in a bowl.
After ribs partially cook, drain.
In a large bowl or pan, arrange ribs with meaty side down.
Pour in barbecue sauce and marinate overnight, covered.
Cook in slow oven (300°
to 325°) until tender. Additional salt or spices may be added.
Can be cooked in crock-pot.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add water, brown sugar, pecans and coconut.
Mix and blend ingredients with a fork; spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes so topping begins to set.
Then turn out onto a cookie sheet.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not use mixer).
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at least 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in boiling water for 10 minutes, covered.
Drain and mash.
Add margarine, eggs, milk and seasoning; mix.
Pour into slightly greased casserole dish.
Combine cheese and bread crumbs as a topping.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375° or until light brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° until filling is firm and brown on top.

title: streuseled apples
directions: In 8-inch square dish place apples.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup brown sugar on top.
With pastry blender, mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle it over the top of the apples.
Microwave at High for 9 to 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Enjoy!

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onion. Mix egg and milk. Pour over bread and let soften. Add more milk if necessary. Add salt and pepper. Mix with hamburger meat. Put in covered baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done. Cover with cheese and return to oven until cheese has melted.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together, except sour cream and mayonnaise.
Let set overnight.
When ready to serve, drain and add sour cream and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add beans, tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Let simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Put in casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: bumstead burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill hamburger buns and wrap in foil. Bake in a 250° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken purlo (bog)
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove skin and bones.
Leave in small pieces. Reserve liquid.
Cool and remove fat.
Fry bacon.
Saute onion with bacon.
Add mushrooms.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Add egg, sugar, milk, shortening, flour, salt and baking powder in a mixing bowl.
Mix until creamy. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch square baking dish that has been sprayed with a vegetable spray.

title: cream drop candy
directions: Melt all in bowl in microwave. Smooth and let cool.

title: sweet potatoes-and-apple casserole
directions: Layer half each of sweet potatoes and apples in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and white pepper. Sprinkle half of mixture over potatoes and apples. Drizzle with half of the margarine.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings with 120 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: cheese minute morsels
directions: *Will be in plastic container in dairy case; can use the squeeze tubes.

title: french bread
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar; let stand until bubbly.
Add flour and salt.
Mix together and knead until smooth and elastic. Let raise until double in bulk.
Make into long loaves on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Chop onion and green peppers.
In skillet, put 1 teaspoon of oil, add peppers and onion and saute about 1 minute.
Add hamburger.
Cook until meat loses its red color, but do not brown.
Turn off skillet.
Add egg; stir well.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Pour butter over nuts in a bowl, sprinkle the sugar and cinnamon over the nuts.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks and gradually add the sugar.
Fold nuts into egg whites.
Spread out on baking sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray
x
13-inch
pan
with Pam.
Cover bottom with croutons and cover with scrambled egg mixture.
Crumble cooked sausage and sprinkle over top.

Pour a little egg mixture over top and sprinkle cheese,ham, onion and green pepper over top. Pour egg mixture on top and sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate chicken for a couple of hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered).

title: 9 layer dutch dinner
directions: In a large baking dish layer first 5 ingredients.
Top with stewed tomatoes (cut into chunks - with juice) Pour 1 small can tomato juice over the top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours on 350. Uncover and bake for another half hour.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large mixing bowl. Add milk, blending thoroughly.
Add warm water in small amounts. Knead dough until soft, but not sticky.
Cover bowl.
Let stand about 15 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Cook and stir hamburger until light brown; drain.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Divide dough into halves.
Pat each half into an 11-inch circle on lightly greased cookie sheet with floured fingers.
Spread sauce over in circles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, hamburger, onion, green pepper and Mozzarella cheese. Cook in 425° oven until cheese is light brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 2 pizzas.

title: stew
directions: Heat shortening in a Dutch oven or a large pot; add garlic and meat and brown very well on all sides.
Add salt, pepper, lemon juice and bay leaf; stir in about 1 1/2 cups boiling water, or enough to just barely cover mixture in pan.
Cover and reduce heat to low; simmer about 1 hour for lamb or 2 hours for beef.
Uncover and remove bay leaf; add potatoes, carrots and celery.
If necessary, add a small amount of boiling water, not more than 1 cup should be required.
Cover and continue cooking over low heat for 25 minutes, or until vegetables are well done.
Add peas. Stir flour into cold water to make a paste.
Add to stew to thicken.
Add additional seasonings, if desired before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: honky tonk
directions: Cook hamburg; drain well.
In double boiler, heat soup and cheese until melted.
Cook the shell macaroni.
Add all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: jello cake
directions: Follow recipe on cake box.
Use 13-inch pan.
Let cake cool. Poke holes in cake with fork.
Mix jello with 1 cup of hot water and 1 cup of cold water mix.
Then pour over cake.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Frost with Cool Whip and then serve.
Serves 12.

title: seafood and spinach log
directions: You will also need string and double thick cheesecloth and 2 roasting pans (same size).

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9-inch deep dish or 10-inch pie pan.
Beat together at medium speed for 2 minutes the flour, baking powder, pudding, margarine, egg and milk.
Pour into pan. Arrange drained sliced peaches over the batter.
(Reserve 3 tablespoons of peach juice.)

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt the butter.
Add flour and cook until bubbly.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add pepper, Madeira and lemon juice.
Add egg yolks, crabmeat, ham and chicken.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Fold in the crab mixture and pour into an unbuttered 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes with pan sitting in a pan of water.
Serve with Newburg sauce or a thin white cream sauce with slivers of pineapple added to it.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender;
remove skin and bones.
Mix Ritz crackers
with
melted
margarine
and
poppy
seed.
Mix chicken, sour
cream
and
chicken soup.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with a layer of cracker mixture.
Spread on chicken mixture;
top
with remaining cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good to make ahead and freeze before baking.

title: layered salad
directions: This recipe was in the drawer for some years, but I'm fairly sure it was in one of the "Three Rivers" cookbooks.
As I mentioned in some other recipes, if you don't have them, get them.
Anyhow, it's a great dish.
The marinating makes the meat tender and very tasty.
Since the steak varies in thickness, you end up with a choice of well done to medium, or even rare.

title: cinnamon delights
directions: Mix together first four ingredients until creamy.
Trim edges off bread (spare bread works best).
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Brush with melted margarine.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
The "pastries" may be placed on a cookie sheet until frozen and stored in a Ziploc bag. When ready to use, no need to thaw.

title: grilled turkey tenderloin
directions: In a shallow pan, blend all marinade ingredients together. Add turkey, turning to coat both sides. Cover. Marinate in the refrigerator several hours or overnight, turning occasionally. Grill the tenderloins over hot coals 8 to 10 minutes per side, depending on the thickness. Tenderloins are done when there is no pink in the center. Do not overcook. Serve in 1/4-inch thick slices in toasted buns. Yields 4 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain 1 can of beans and keep the liquid of the other.
Place both cans of beans in a casserole and heat.
Mix the ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add to the beans and sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; blend the soup and mayonnaise.
Combine with 1/2 cup cheese and other ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rapee morvandelle for 4(quiche)
directions: Cook onion, oil and butter until tender; add diced cooked ham and brown.
Beat together eggs, garlic, parsley, chives, grated cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Add ham and onion.
Add potatoes (or hash browns or frozen taters) and mix., Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large pie plate (glass preferably) or skillet.
When butter foams, add egg and potato mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute	onions	 in
oleo
until
transparent.	Combine onions, rice
and
hot
broth.
Bring to boil on top of range. Cover and place in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve and listen to the compliments.
Serves 4 hungry or 6 polite people.

title: buffalo chips cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugars.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift salt, flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to bowl.
Mix well. Stir in oats, cornflakes, pecans, chocolate morsels and coconut.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add all eggs (mix).
Add half of the flour and all milk.
Mix well and add remaining flour.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: sucre a la creme
directions: Heat on low in a sauce pan.
Stir and test by putting some to your lips, if it feels like sugar, put in sink with cold water on the outside of pan.
Stir until the fudge is thick.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 cooking pan and let cool.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Mix together ice cream topping and condensed milk.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in bottom of saucepan; saute celery and onion. Add water and bouillon.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Sprinkle in parsley.
Stir in half and half.
Add broccoli and carrots last.

title: sweet crackers
directions: Break crackers apart and lay in cookie sheet.
Combine butter and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add vanilla.
Pour over crackers. Cook in oven for about 7 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with pecans.
Decorative sprinkles are good for children.

title: really italian bread
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place bread, cut side up, on baking sheet.
Set aside.
In small bowl, mix together the garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper; drizzle mixture over sliced bread.
Sprinkle bread with scallions and tomatoes, then top with cheese.
Bake in upper half of oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese melts and edges of bread brown.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and serve.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add milk and mix well.
Add vanilla, cherries and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.
Cookies can be rolled in cornflakes before baking.

title: sticky biscuits
directions: Lay biscuits out on waxed paper and flatten each biscuit with the palm of your hand.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Dip marshmallow halves in melted margarine and then roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place in center of flattened biscuit. Fold biscuit around marshmallow, sealing by pinching biscuit edges together.
Dip biscuit in margarine and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place each biscuit in muffin pan (pinched edges down). Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from muffin cups while still hot.

title: pancakes
directions: Add milk and vinegar; stir.
Put in egg, salt, sugar and oil. Mix; add flour to desired thickness, about 1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: filipino pancit
directions: Saute in oil the garlic and onion.
Add pork, chicken and ham and saute 1 minute.
Add carrot, zucchini and cabbage.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add softened rice sticks, soy sauce, chicken broth and salt and pepper.
Mix well and cook another 10 to 15 minutes. Arrange in serving dish.
Garnish with hard-cooked eggs.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Pour broccoli in pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Top with chicken pieces, melted butter, cheese and soups until blended and pour over top. Cover with croutons.
Bake at 350°
and bake for 35 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In a 4 quart dish, place brown sugar, butter, corn syrup, water, and salt.
Microwave at high 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes.
Add soda.
Pour over popcorn and peanuts (optional), and toss.
Spread on aluminum foil to cool or form into balls.

title: recipe for a good class
directions: Take 21 unique students and one patient, caring teacher and combine them in a bright, cheerful classroom.
Blend 2 1/3 cups of self control and 2 cups of patience.
Mix 1 pound of honesty and 2 pounds of forgiveness.
Pour in 4 gallons of good behavior and 2 gallons of politeness.
Stir in
32 ounces of kindness and 24 ounces of friendliness.
Carefully add one quart of attentiveness and 1 pint of obedience.

Bake at 75° for nine weeks to get 22 good listeners (teacher included) with wonderful self esteem. Sprinkle lightly with "No Tattle Dust" and review recipe often. Should serve 21 Summer Grove families.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the liquid.
In a saucepan, saute the green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Blend in the soup and 1/3 to 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Add the chicken, pineapple tidbits and soy sauce.
Heat, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice.
Top with almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Mix all together and put in graham cracker crust.
Freeze. Top with small dollop of Cool Whip and a cherry or strawberry when serving.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Wash mushrooms clean. Slice large ones.
Cream the butter and flour. Add grated onion, milk and salt. Cook over low flame until thick, at least 5 minutes. Add drained fresh mushrooms that have been cooked in salted water.
Turn into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with well mixed grated cheese and crumbs. Bake in a 325° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, except oats, to mixture.
By hand, stir in oats, chips and nuts.
For large cookies, use an ice cream scoop.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate, nuts, vanilla and marshmallows after taking the mixture off heat.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cream butter, flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Then put over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Peel and core tomatoes.
Peel and finely chop onions.
Finely chop bell peppers and red peppers.
Then add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Stir ingredients thoroughly.
Cook until thick.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: jan's cake recipe
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package, adding 1/2 cup coconut to the batter.
Cook as directed on package.
While still hot and still in the pan, pour the Coco Lopez over the cake after punching holes as deep as possible with a fork.
Let cake cool, then cover with La Creme whipped topping and top with the rest of the coconut.
Chill.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Put Cool Whip last.
Chill overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and set aside.
Chop up lettuce, onion, tomatoes and olives and mix in large bowl (salad grows); add picante sauce, shredded cheese, Italian dressing and ground beef.
Crush bag of Doritos and stir in mixture.
Heat in microwave for about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (you don't want the salad too soft and mushy).

title: cheddar pea salad
directions: Combine all together.
Chill 1 hour or longer.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixer bowl; blend. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Combine last 3 ingredients.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer ingredients as shown.
Pour condensed milk over all. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift and mix dry ingredients.
In bowl, mix egg, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix slowly with spoon by hand to just combine, do not beat.
Grease muffin tins or large iron skillet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Using a tablespoon, scoop out and shape meat balls.
Fry in butter or oil until brown, frying only a few at a time.
Place in a chafing dish to keep warm.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yields 30 to 35 meat balls.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, margarine and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spoon evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased with margarine.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and store in refrigerator.
Makes 40 squares.

title: glenda's pecan snackers
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks. Mix in brown sugar, flour and vanilla. Fold in pecans. Remove 1 at a time and place well-coated an inch apart on brown paper on a cookie sheet. Bake in a slow oven for 30 minutes. Turn off oven and let stackers stand for 30 minutes in oven. Take out and let cool.

title: oven fried potatoes
