directions: Halve potatoes lengthwise and slice into 1/2-inch thick strips.
Put margarine, oil, salt and pepper in bowl.
Add potatoes, tossing to coat well.
Arrange potato strips in single layer on nonstick baking sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 450° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hedgehogs(cookies)
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, cocoa and egg.
Crumble cookies in a tea towel.
Add mixtures together with vanilla.
Press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut in small squares.
May be iced.
Do not cook.

title: taco layer bean dip
directions: On a platter, mix beans and taco seasonings thoroughly and spread in an even layer.
Spread each of the following layers evenly in order:
sour half and half, salsa, shredded cheese, chopped tomatoes, green onions and ripe olives.
Serve with chips.

title: spicy cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, black-eyed peas, peanuts and peppers in a salad bowl.
Mix well.
Whip vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and olive oil in a small bowl.
Add peanut oil in a thin stream, whisking until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables, tossing to coat.
Chill until serving time.

title: pone bread
directions: Mix
cornmeal,	salt and margarine.
Add boiling water. Stir the
ingredients.
Wet
your hands and shape into patties about 1/2-inch
thick.
Fry in oil until golden, turning once. Remove and drain.

title: curried lima bean casserole
directions: Cook limas as directed.
Drain and save liquid.
Combine onion, red pepper, soup and water in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly. Remove from heat; blend sour cream and curry powder into soup mixture.
Stir in limas.
Turn mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine crumbs with melted butter.
Add crumbled bacon. Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: five hour stew
directions: Place stew meat in bottom of pan.
Add layers of onion, carrots, potatoes and celery.
Sprinkle tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper on top.
Spread soup over top.
Pour water down sides.
Do not stir!
Bake at 225° for 5 hours or on high in crock-pot for 4 1/2 hours and low for 1/2 hour.
Stir and serve.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and add the margarine.
Bake and cool in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread on top of cooled cake.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add the remaining ingredients and blend together.
Place in a floured pan shaped in a loaf. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
While still hot, cut biscuits to thickness desired.

title: barbecue sauce(this recipe is great with beef, pork, ribs, chicken, etc.)
directions: In a saucepan, heat all ingredients.
Use for barbecued meats or on ribs or on grilled hamburgers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and pecans together; press in pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Spread pie filling on top.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Beat egg and mix with sour cream. Spread over top.
Bake 30 more minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Save liquid.
Sprinkle 1/3 of cracker crumbs evenly in the bottom of casserole.
Top with layer of asparagus. Spread 1/2 mushroom soup evenly over asparagus.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons asparagus liquid.
Repeat layering, ending with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: strawberry sauce(use on pork tenderloin or to bake ham.)
directions: Mix in medium saucepan all the ingredients together and cook over low heat until thickened, approximately 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Mash berries with a spoon. You may store in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend flour, salt, cocoa and sugar.
Add to scalded milk. Cook until it thickens.
Add small amount of mixture to egg yolks. Mix and return to pan.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Let cool and pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue.

title: speculaasjes(dutch christmas cookies; makes 6 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; blend in sour cream.
Mix and sift dry ingredients (do not use electric beater, too stiff).
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Wrap in foil.
Chill several hours.
Work with 1 portion at a time.
Roll out thin.
Cut into fancy shapes. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Roll scrapes in a ball and chill before using.

title: skillet squash au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add summer squash, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cook, covered, 12 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with cheese and a little soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deluxe fajita nachos
directions: In medium skillet, combine chicken, spices and seasonings for fajitas and water.
Blend well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
In large shallow ovenproof platter, arrange chips.
Top with chicken and cheeses.
Place under broiler to melt cheese.
Top with tomatoes, olives, green onions and desired amount of salsa.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain fat.
Add celery, onions, chili sauce, molasses, soup and water. Simmer for short time.
Add 1 1/2 cups Minute rice.
Mix all together in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick together.
Next melt cheese and add to mixture.
Form balls and cook 10 minutes at 350°.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream together well.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating 5 minutes after each.
Turn into cooled, baked pie shell.
Cool 1 to 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream and walnuts.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, over medium heat for 236° on candy thermometer or until mixture dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Do not stir for 15 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss (about 8 minutes).
Stir in the cherries and walnuts.
Quickly pour into a shallow pan (greased).
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Add oleo and cool.
Pour over diced apples.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: bean and rice salad
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart covered container, combine cooked rice, beans, peas, celery, onion, diced green chili peppers and parsley. Add the dressing to the rice mixture; toss gently to mix. Cover and chill for up to 24 hours. To serve, transfer the chilled salad to a serving bowl. Garnish with cilantro sprigs and whole chili peppers. Makes 16 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2-quart, covered dish.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion lightly in a 4-quart kettle. Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 40 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine; boil one minute.
Mix cocoa, vanilla, oats and nuts, then add to sugar mixture.

title: candied violet
directions: Do not attempt to remove green calyx from violet.
Mix egg whites, water and extract.
Brush on violets, covering each flower well.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, completely covering both sides.
They can be dried in the open air a week or two, in a sunny window in 2 or 3 days or in the oven at 200° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Set aside.
Slice by hand or food processor as for slaw the lettuce, cauliflower and onion into a large bowl.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Crumble on bacon. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Add mayonnaise and mix well. Serve.

title: low-fat chicken and rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice, using package directions, adding onion and green pepper.
Combine rice and soups in a bowl; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon into a baking dish; top with chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and bananas. Add flour and other ingredients after sifting together.
Add gradually.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in a large heavy saucepan until done.
Use a lot of water to cook chicken (about 4 quarts).
Set aside to cool.

title: szechwan beef stir-fry
directions: Cut beef steak lengthwise into 2 strips.
Slice across the grain into 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, 2 teaspoons oil, sugar and cornstarch and stir into strips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix margarine and crackers together.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: haley's quick spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients in microwavable dish.
Add meat.
Cook on 50% power for 30 minutes. Serve over spaghetti.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix with marshmallows, coconut and cottage cheese.
Serve immediately or pour into mold and chill from 8 to 10 hours in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
Cream butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs gradually.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Cut butter into dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 cup and mix with walnuts.
Pat remainder into 9x13-inch pan, building 1/2 inch of edge.
Spread pie filling within 1/2 inch of edge.
Sprinkle reserved mix over top.
Bake at 350 degrees 30 to 40 minutes.

title: "crispy pretzel bars"
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine the sugar and corn syrup. Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Stir in peanut butter until blended. Add the cereal, pretzels and M&M's; stir until coated. Press into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Cut into bars. Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: madi's cinnamon apples
directions: Toss apple with lemon juice; set aside.
Melt margarine in a nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add sugar and cinnamon; stir well.
Add apple; cook 7 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 2 servings (about 106 calories per 1/2-cup serving).

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: In the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt 1/2 stick oleo. Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes. Pour first mixture over cornflakes.
Slice 1/2 stick oleo into pats and place on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, dry them and put in a gallon jar. Add the alum, salt and pickling spice.
Fill jar with vinegar.
Leave in jar 3 months. Drain off vinegar.
Slice cucumbers and put back in jar. Add the sugar and let sugar melt.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Heat chips, salt and milk on low heat.
When melted, turn off heat and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in wax paper lined pan and chill 2 hours.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and cream of tartar in mixer bowl.
Drop in margarine.
Add about 2/3 of milk and vanilla; beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl.
Scrape beater at end of each stage.
Add eggs and remaining milk; beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 2 deep 8-inch pans in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of glass casserole dish.
Cover with 1 can Hormel chili (no beans).
Sprinkle to cover with grated cheese.
Heat in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts. Serve with taco chips.

title: lower calorie fudge
directions: Mix in heavy 2-quart pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a quick boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir chocolate bits in until completely melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and salt; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, pepper and onions.
Refrigerate overnight.
This makes a lot and will keep 1 to 2 weeks.

title: tuna salad and rice
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Makes 2 quarts.
Serves 12.

title: old-fashion lemonade
directions: Mix according to instructions on frozen concentrate and Fla-Vor Aid drink mix. Add 1 cup of sugar as only needed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and add remainder of ingredients.
Roll into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients completely. Add milk, vanilla, egg yolks and margarine. Stir over low heat until thick, then pour into pie crust. Cover with meringue and bake until meringue begins to brown.

title: sour cream streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Reserve 2 tablespoons dry cake mix for filling.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Work cheese and flour together until crumbly.
Add butter and stir well with fork.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at least 1/2 hour at 350°.
Allow to sit 5 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef with taco seasoning; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine soups and tomatoes; stir well.
Layer Doritos in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour meat mixture on top of chips. Pour soup and tomato mixture on top of meat.
Lastly, sprinkle cheese over top and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 pint ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick. Stir in zucchini, pineapple, flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, currants and walnuts.
Blend well.
Pour into two greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven one hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes two loaves.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Grease and flour pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add soda, cinnamon, salt and flour; mix well.
Add chopped apples and mix again.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. When cake starts to bake, top with brown sugar and nuts (optional).

title: chicken-broccoli
directions: Brown
chicken;
add
milk, bouillon cube, broccoli and rice. Stir
and
simmer until tender.
Remove from heat for 5 minutes. Add mayonnaise and cheese.

title: oklahoma beans
directions: Use crock-pot, put beans in.
Cook bacon and onions until onions are limp.
Add molasses, Worcestershire sauce, chili sauce or powder, garlic and ketchup.
Turn on low and forget it.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients well and shape into 1-inch balls, place on cookie sheet.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, corn syrup and water in saucepan. Bring to boil; cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved; cool.
Place sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Pour gelatin mixture over all. Stand strawberries (same size) with stems attached around pie crust.
Serve with whipped cream.
Never had a slice leftover.

title: caroline seafood muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread on buttered, toasted muffin halves.
Put under broiler until golden brown.

title: hershey chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool before spreading on cake.
Makes enough for 4 layer cake.

title: yesterday cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix egg and sugar, pineapple and Cool Whip together.
Add nuts last.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and pour mixture over them.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and simmer.
Layer in a 9x13 pan, sauce, noodles and cheese, repeat.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: cream of "whatever" soup
directions: Place diced vegetable in water and simmer until vegetable is cooked (about 1 1/2 hours).
Remove from heat.
In separate 2-quart saucepan, melt butter; add onion and saute until transparent.
Add flour and blend well.
Add vegetable and all broth; blend until mixture thickens.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in hot half and half.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in small bowl.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar into large bowl.
Mix in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in buttermilk to yeast mixture, then add to flour mixture.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Roll about 1/4- 1/2 inch thick.
Place on greased baking dish.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours. Bake in 400 degree oven about 15 minutes.
Makes about 15 biscuits.
Some of the dough can be refrigerated and baked another time if you wish.

title: quick and easy creamed chicken over biscuits
directions: Bake biscuits as directed.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, milk and seasonings in a microwave dish.
Microwave for 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve creamed chicken over the hot biscuits. Add a salad and you have a quick and easy supper!

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble 1 to 1 1/2 cups corn bread into a big salad bowl.

In another bowl, combine tomatoes, pepper, onion, pickles and bacon. Spoon half of vegetable mixture over corn bread. Stir together the mayonnaise and pickle juice in small bowl. Spread half of this dressing over the vegetables in big bowl. Repeat layering remaining corn bread, vegetables and dressing. Cover tightly and chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
When done, add butter and garlic cheese.
Beat eggs and milk; add to grits.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until set.

title: cheddar cheese with port
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually beat in the Cheddar cheese with the Port.
Shape mixture into balls; coat with the finely chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: grandma mcmillen's orange sauce
directions: Combine the orange juice, sugar, cornstarch, salt and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add butter and orange rind and let cool.
Mix in 1 can mandarin oranges and drizzle over angle food cake.

title: 5 week bran muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl or dishpan.
Stir and mix well.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in order given. Mix well.
Set 2 or 3 hours before baking.
Bake in greased muffin tins 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen.
Store in refrigerator up to 5 weeks.
Use as needed.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: steak parmigiana
directions: Pound meat to 1/4-inch thick
and trim off fat.
Cut in pieces.
Dip in egg and
roll
in
mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Brown in oil
with the onions (both sides of meat).
Place
in
x 13-inch baking dish.
To the same oil, add spices and tomato paste.
Add water, stirring constantly. Boil for
minutes, scraping brown bits from bottom of pan. Pour
2/3 of
sauce
over
meat.
Top
with cheese slices and remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix sugar, flour and pineapple; pour into dish. Add cheese; crumble crackers on top. Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: breakfast egg bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter both sides of bread and place 6 slices into greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Place 6 slices of the cheese on top and half of the meat mixture.
Repeat with remaining bread, cheese and meat.
Now take the 12 eggs and whip them.
Add to mixture 5 cups of whole milk.
Beat well; pour over bread and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until eggs are solid.

title: no bake fudge
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and Quik in microwave. Stir in powdered sugar. Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: spinach bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix spinach, eggs, soup, onion, cheese and dressing.
Spoon spinach mixture into greased 8-inch square pan. Top with combined bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt; drain well.
Place broccoli in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Stir together soup, milk, mayonnaise, beaten egg and cheese until well blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over soup mixture.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 45 minutes until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: whipping cream pound cake(elvis' favorite)
directions: Butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Thoroughly cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in half the flour, then the cream, then the other half of the flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Set in cold oven and turn heat to 350°.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes until sharp knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: christmas cookie balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Butter hands and roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin ina double boiler.
Place a few balls at a time into the hot chocolate mixture.
Lift out with a fork onto wax paper to dry.
Always keep chocolate mixture hot.
Makes about 60 balls.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add water, shortening, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix together until well blended and bake at 350° for 30 to 36 minutes.

title: fajita pot roast
directions: Marinate fajita meat in fajita seasoning and lime juice for at least 1 hour.
Put roast in roasting pan with the onions, green peppers and celery.
Pour over top the picante sauce.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cut in strips and serve with flour tortillas.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Continue to stir until melted.
Add marshmallow, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut.

title: half moon cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Frost.

title: home cooked roast beef
directions: Cut chuck roast into chunks.
Put it into big pan or crock-pot.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, then pour over meat.
Heat to a boil, then cover and simmer for 6 hours or you could bake it in the oven for 6 hours at 300°.
When you can shred the meat apart with a fork, it's done.
Shred all your meat and mix.

title: sausage bread
directions: Filling:
Brown sausage and chop into little pieces.
Drain and set aside.
Boil spinach and drain well.
Saute onion.
Mix all three ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and grated cheese.

title: summer vegetable medley
directions: Oil a covered casserole large enough to hold mixture.
Combine rice and vegetables in casserole.
Pour consomme over mixture. Cover casserole.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove casserole from oven.
Stir gently and return to oven, uncovered, for about 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: mexican pork stew
directions: Brown pork in oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pintos or big limas
directions: Cook beans real good.
Take out any that are not good.
Wash real good 3 or 4 times.
Put beans in crock-pot, 6-quart size. Fill almost to top with water.
Cook for 8 hours or until done. Then add honey and chicken style seasoning.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Melt butter. Fry potatoes until nearly done. Break the eggs over them and stir quickly.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: cream of mushroom spinach
directions: Brown
hamburger
with	garlic;
drain	fat.
Stir in 2 boxes spinach
and 2 cans cream of mushroom soup;
let simmer for
5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot rice.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder; mix until smooth. Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn the mixture into the pan. Spoon the pie filling onto the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Into a mixture of 1 3/4 cups of water and the juice of one lemon, slice 3 large ripe bananas.
This is to keep the bananas and the bread turning dark when cooked.

title: jello ice cream dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water (using 8 to 9-inch metal pan which helps the gelatin cool faster).
Remove 1/2 cup and pour into a bowl.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to gelatin in the pan and place in the freezer until thick, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage, peppers and rice casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. In a large casserole, heat the Italian sausage with 1/4 cup water over high heat and cook for 6 minutes, or until the water is gone. Remove the sausage and let cool slightly. Slice the sausage into 1 inch pieces and set aside.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Put wax paper on bottom.
Blend sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
(If desired, add nuts and/or candied fruit.)
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Great for brunch.

title: turkey cutlets with cranberry sauce
directions: If turkey cutlets are thick, with meat mallet or dull edge of French knife, pound them to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut cutlets into 3 x 3-inch pieces.
On waxed paper, combine flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Dip turkey pieces into flour mixture to coat.

In nonstick 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook turkey cutlets, half at a time, 2 to 3 minutes until turkey cutlets are lightly browned and lose their pink color throughout; remove to bowl.
In the same skillet, stir cranberry sauce, lemon juice, cornstarch, chicken flavor bouillon, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 cup water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens slightly.
Boil 1 minute.
Return turkey cutlets to skillet; heat through.
Spoon mixture onto warm platter.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving contains about 290 calories, 9 g fat, 68 mg cholesterol and 630 mg sodium.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions; drain. (Cool in a single layer on wax paper to keep parsley, salt and pepper.)
Fill each shell with cheese mixture.

title: diet lemon pie
directions: Use your own lemon pie recipe or use 1 box of lemon Jell-O pie filling.
Cook as directed except use 3 eggs instead of 2 and omit sugar.
Cook over medium heat until done.
Stir well.
Set mixture aside to cool 5 minutes.
Stir and add 11 packages of Equal sweetener (or sweeten pie as desired).
Fix meringue, using your recipe.
Place on pie.
Brown in oven at 350° for about 5 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Sprinkle drained sausage over rolls.
Lightly beat the eggs and pour over sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
It's quick and delicious.

title: calzones
directions: Brown sausage, add onion and garlic, saute.
Stir in sauce and spices.
Simmer 5 minutes; remove from heat and cool.
Add the cheese and beaten whole egg.
Mix well.
Punch down thawed dough and divide into 6 equal pieces.
Roll into a circle.
Spoon filling onto dough.
Brush edges with egg white and fold in half, pinching edges to seal with a fork.
Brush egg yolk and milk mixture lightly on top.
Prick with fork.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 425° for 12 minutes.
Pepperoni, peppers, mushrooms and olives can also be added.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumber slices.
Stir well. Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Ladle into large, stemmed glasses. Garnish with cucumber slices.
Yields 9 cups.

title: chewy peanut butter squares
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add flour and coconut; mix well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in oven at 350° for 22 minutes.

title: moravian white cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and nutmeg.

Set aside. In a large bowl with wooden spoon or portable electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth and fluffy. With wooden spoon, stir in half of flour mixture. Then add rest of flour mixture, mixing with hands, if necessary. Refrigerate dough, covered, for several hours or overnight.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Then mix with eggs and oil, beaten together.
Then add zucchini and onion.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate or 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: spinach and mushroom lasagna roll-ups
directions: In a medium skillet over moderate heat, saute mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil until mushrooms give off their juices and darken and onions are tender, about 7 to 8 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. The salt will help draw water out of the vegetables as they cook. Add dry chopped spinach to the pan and heat through for 1 minute. Adjust seasonings with salt, pepper and a little nutmeg. Add Ricotta and stir into mixture to heat cheese through 1 minute longer. Remove pan from heat, but leave in warm skillet. Heat broth in a small pan over moderate heat. Melt alfredo sauce into broth and bring liquid to a bubble. Thicken sauce about 2 minutes. Place cooked lasagna noodles on a large work surface or cutting board. Spread lasagna noodles with a layer of spinach-mushroom filling. Roll up pasta and arrange the bundles in a shallow casserole dish. Pour warm sauce over roll-ups and top with Mozzarella. Place casserole under the broiler to melt cheese.

title: texas pinto beans
directions: Boil beans according to directions until done.
Saute onion in small amount of margarine or oil until transparent.
Add ground beef.
Cook until brown.
Add browned beef and onions to cooked beans.
Add Rotel and can of tomatoes.
Simmer to allow flavors to blend.
use salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: all-n.b.a.  wild rice
directions: In a 1 3/4-quart casserole, melt butter and add all ingredients including liquid.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.
This recipe can be easily doubled.

title: garbanzo beans
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and garlic.
Add 4 to 5 drops of soy sauce as desired. Set aside. Drain the beans. Add chopped onion and chopped parsley to taste. Pour dressing over beans. Salt to taste. Chill overnight.

title: ranch potato salad primavera
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Makes about 8 cups salad.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries through a food chopper or blender.
Add remaining ingredients and allow to stand a day or two in the refrigerator to blend flavors.
This is a very good dish.

title: hot beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter.
Mix in cheese, soup, milk and seasonings.
Mix with noodles.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with Chinese noodles, place in oven and heat well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions. Let cool. Pour crushed pineapple over cake (do not drain pineapple). When vanilla pudding has cooled, pour that mixture over pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 8 hours on low.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well; bake in buttered baking dish at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top may be sprinkled with more crumbs, more cheese or both.
This can be mixed ahead of time except for topping, then topped and baked when ready to serve.

title: herbed home fries
directions: Dice potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes or slice 1/4 inch thick. Saute potatoes over medium heat in butter, margarine or oil.
Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Saute potatoes until golden brown.
Add 2 teaspoons minced herbs, such as chives and/or thyme. Stir to coat potatoes with herbs and serve immediately.

title: creamy hamburger noodle dish(microwave)
directions: Crumble hamburger into 2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion and garlic.
Microwave uncovered until
meat is firm, 5 to 6 minutes. Stir to break up meat.
Drain.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoons into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding in whipped topping; whip.
Add pineapple with juice and whip until fluffy.
Add pecans.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold and chill.
May also be served as a dessert.
Serves 8.

title: easy shrimp and pasta
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on.
Combine all ingredients, except pasta, in
a shallow casserole. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Pour over cooked pasta. Serves 4 people.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in dish.
Bake in 375° oven
until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Pour in Ragu.
Heat.
Boil noodles until tender.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of noodles on bottom, layer of hamburger meat mixture.
Spread half of the cottage cheese mixture next, then a layer of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat the 4 layers again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour french dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and whisk until smooth.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups. Great dip for chicken tenders or chicken nuggets.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a separate bowl mix eggs, oil, vanilla, carrots, raisins, walnuts, coconut and apple.
Then add to the flour mixture.
Bake in greased or lined muffin tins at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Mix; let stand 20 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix juice, water and sugar together. Stir until dissolved. Serve over ice.

title: children's play dough
directions: Put all ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from pan.
Knead immediately.
Store in airtight container in cool place (keeps for weeks).

title: southern cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a large roasting pan. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Makes enough to serve large family gatherings.

title: swedish crescents
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla, flour, nuts and salt; mix.
Chill well.
Shape dough into crescents, using 1/2 teaspoon dough.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Check to be sure they do not brown.
When done, roll in 1 cup confectioners sugar to which 1 teaspoon of vanilla has been added.
Makes between 6 and 7 dozen.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and cut in half lengthwise.
Hollow out shells, reserving the pulp.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until soft.
Add chopped zucchini pulp and chopped tomato to mixture.
It should not be too juicy.
Fill shells with mixture, rounding the top.

title: pot roast
directions: Season to
taste.
Roast
with	pepper, salt or no salt seasoning
mix.
Coat
roast
with	flour.	Heat
cup	of vegetable oil
on
high heat in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven. Brown roast
quickly on each side.	Remove roast from container; drain
excess
oil	off.
Leave
drippings	in container. Slice 3 medium
onions.
Layer
on bottom of skillet or Dutch oven half of the onions.
Place roast back in container.
Put the remaining onions on top of roast.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook and mash.
Add cream cheese, egg and onions.
Bake until fluffy or about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bulgur pilaf
directions: Combine bulgur and stock.
Let soak approximately 45 minutes until liquid is absorbed.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook together the hamburger, onions, celery, salt and pepper to taste until meat is browned, stirring often. Add the sugar, brown sugar, ketchup, vinegar and dry mustard.
Simmer 2 hours. Serves 100.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Shape into a log by rolling between waxed paper.
Roll log in chili powder until coated.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter Crisco.
Add and mix egg, vanilla and pecans.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake at 375°.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar together until mushy.
Add Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Makes 4 cups.
Freeze or refrigerate.
It could also be stored on shelf if you cover with wax.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Shake crackers in brown paper bag.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over crackers. Shake and store in airtight container.

title: almost cabbage rolls
directions: Precook cabbage until wilted. Season and cook meat, onions, and bell pepper until meat is done and veggies are tender. Add chili powder, water, tomato sauce, Rotel tomatoes, and rice. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until rice is done and water is cooked out.

title: turkey stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise to form oval boats; remove seeds.
Boil them for 5 minutes or microwave them.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In 10-inch frypan, saute onions and garlic for 2 minutes. Add ground turkey, tomato paste and corn, stirring frequently; cook 5 minutes.
Add rice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; cook 2 minutes on low heat.
Fill each pepper boat with 1/4 of cooked turkey mixture.
Sprinkle each with cheese and broil or microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Serves 4. Contains 189 calories each serving.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water (or steam if fresh), and drain. Combine vegetables, nuts, and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard, and garlic together and pour over salad mixture.
Toss gently.
Chill.

title: ol st. nick's gingerbread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Grease 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or
ice cream.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender, drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients except 1 cup grated cheese.
Add seasoning to desired taste. Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
May be refrigerated overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: david's dump salad
directions: Beat cottage cheese and whipped topping until blended.
Add jello and stir well.
Mold in pineapple and mandarin oranges; chill.

title: cheesecake
directions: Stir together 1 1/4 cups graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/3 cup melted margarine and pat in bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside and prepare filling.

title: apple fiber raisin muffins(cholesterol lowering)
directions: Purchase apple fiber from Tastee Apple Inc. Newcomerstown, Ohio.
$1 per pound.

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Use nonstick muffin tins.
Add a little oil and heat muffin pan, then add muffin mix.
Bake at 450°.
Remove from pan while still hot.

title: round steak dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Dutch oven for 3 hours at 250° or put in crock-pot for 4 or 5 hours on high.
Serve over mashed potatoes, noodles or rice.

title: super chuck roast
directions: Brown meat; add carrots, potatoes and onions.
Mix soup with one can of water.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Cover.
Cook for 2 hours at 325°.
Delicious!

title: guacamole(an authentic mexican recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve as dip with Doritos or Fritos.
Serve as a salad with other Mexican dishes.

title: tangy low sugar punch
directions: Reconstitute lemonade.
Add pineapple juice, sweetener and food coloring.
Pour over crushed ice and add Sprite.
Yields approximately 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: serendipity soup
directions: Combine broth, soup bone, ham hock, curry, bay leaves, garlic and onion.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Take out bones and remove meat.
Add meat, potatoes, pepperoni, cabbage and beans.
Simmer 1 more hour.

title: cajun chicken dish
directions: Cut green peppers, celery and carrots into chunks.
Boil chicken breasts until done, let cool, then pull off the bone into bite size pieces.
Coat with seasoning mix.
Fry in oil until hot. Add more oil to pan, about 1/3-inch.
Add chunks of vegetables. Mix together.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice, noodles or on tortilla shells.

title: mel's no bake blueberry pie
directions: Prepare pie shell. Wash and drain the blueberries thoroughly. Mix 1 cup berries in a pan with sugar, water, cornstarch and salt. Cook and stir over low heat until thick. Add remaining uncooked berries with butter or margarine. Mix well and cool. Pour in cooled pie shell and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: patio punch
directions: Mix ingredients and add ice. Serve from a punch bowl or pitcher.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Whip milk and Cool Whip.
Stir in fruit; add pecans and lemon juice last.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: my mother's cabbage salad
directions: Bring mayonnaise, mustard, horseradish, cream, salt, pepper and sugar to a boil.
Boil gently for a few minutes.
Chop cabbage, onions and green pepper fine.
Pour dressing over all; toss well.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and milk. Sift together dry ingredients; stir into pumpkin mixture.
Beat 1 minute with electric or rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan, cool.
Slice and serve with butter or whipped cream cheese.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat thoroughly.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle lightly with flour and bake at 350° until done.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl and stir gently, so you do not break up the fruit.
Place in a mold of your choice and let set in the refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water for about 1 hour until tender.
Place in baking dish the cornbread stuffing; pour margarine over stuffing. Remove bone from chicken breasts.
Tear breasts apart and place on top of stuffing.
Combine milk, cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with a little stuffing. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets well. Combine egg, water and vanilla flavoring.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients. Blend brown sugar and oil in a large bowl at low speed.
Add eggs. Beat until smooth. Add flour in 5 parts. Scrape bowl well after each addition. Stir in butterscotch morsels. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute.
Place on cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Let margarine stand at room temperature until softened. Mix 1 stick of margarine with the graham cracker crumbs to form a crust; press into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Place remaining 2 sticks of margarine, powdered sugar, and eggs into a mixing bowl and beat with mixer for 3 minutes; spread over the crust.

title: haystack candy
directions: Melt chips and stir in noodles and nuts.
Chips can be melted in microwave or in double boiler.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix together in bowl.
Set aside about 1/4 cup flour mixture.
Break eggs into another bowl.
Beat lightly.
Measure and pour in honey.
Melt butter in small pan on medium heat and blend in eggs slowly.
Pour egg mixture into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Chop candied fruit and nuts.
Sprinkle with remaining flour mixture. Stir both into batter.
Spread in baking pan and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be served plain or frosted.
Cut in squares.
Makes 40 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Pour over the sliced pickles.
Do not heat.
Makes 1 gallon.
Keeps in fridge for a long time.
Let soak for about a month before starting to eat. Stir occasionally.

title: mom's carrot cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients and sift well.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots last and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool before icing.

title: grandmother's cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then add cold water.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Process fruit (peel, core, devein and chop).
Mix together and add pecans.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 3 layers 30 to 35 minutes or 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: phillip homer's microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, Karo, sugar and salt.
Cook on Full power 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 more minutes.
Add butter and stir until blended.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla, stirring until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Cool!

title: neil stuart's japanese clam and water chestnut chowder(serves 4)
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan over moderate heat.
Add leeks and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and continue cooking for 3 additional minutes.
Stir in flour until it absorbs all the liquid in the pot, then add teriyaki, clam juice, chopped clams, water chestnuts and green onions.
Bring the mixture to a boil and, lowering the heat, simmer for 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice and black pepper and serve.

title: bardstown, kentucky cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, pour Kahlua over cake.
Let cake set overnight.
Break cake into pieces in pan.
Mix pudding as directed and pour over cake. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: haystacks candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over boiling water.
When completely melted, mix all ingredients in and stir well to coat.
Spoon out on wax paper and let cool.
(I like to add some pecans halves to mine.)

title: fillet of venison
directions: Note:
This recipe is great with deer and all other big game. Can be used with elk, moose, sheep and caribou.

title: critter crackers
directions: Combine flours and baking powder.
Beat butter or margarine for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar, honey and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Divide in half.
Cover, chill several hours or overnight.

title: ruth's black bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in microwave proof bowl.
You may sprinkle some extra cheese on top.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Gently mix all ingredients except eggs and potato chips in a large bowl.
Fold in diced eggs.
Pour into buttered flat casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.
Do not freeze.

title: crunchy cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage and green onions.
Toast almonds and sesame seeds until lightly browned; cool.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Chop broccoli.
Combine celery, onion and raisins.
Pour dressing over salad.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mother's icebox cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add egg and mix well, then add dry ingredients and nuts.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Shape into long rolls, each roll will be approximately 1-inch in diameter and about the length of the width of wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes.
Yields 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
A good cookie for mailing.

title: canape lorenzo
directions: Mix with enough mayonnaise so that it will spread nicely. Also, add a little wine or garlic vinegar.
Spread on Melba toast and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and a little paprika. Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: muscadine cake filling
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and butter in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 20 minutes (can use double boiler) until thickened.

title: crisp waffles
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and butter.
Stir in dry ingredients. Fold in egg whites.
Pour over hot waffle iron.

title: 30 minute fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl; set aside.
Bring to a boil, in saucepan, water, Crisco, margarine and cocoa.
Pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in an 11 x 14-inch pan. (Ice while warm.)

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, dry ingredients, water and syrup mixing well. Add nuts, then pour into well greased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Raisins may be used instead of nuts.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In oblong baking dish, melt butter.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour chocolate chips over crumbs and then pour coconut over chocolate chips.
Pour nuts over coconut and then pour sweetened condensed milk over nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: spaghetti squash with beef
directions: Steam squash 20 minutes; set aside to cool.
Brown ground beef; drain and set aside.
Scrape squash out of skin into a bowl. In a large frypan, saute onion in butter until clear.
Add squash, carrot and seasoning to taste.
Stir and cook on medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add beef and cheese.
When cheese melts, serve.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add 1 cup sugar and lemon rind. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add milk. Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix lemon juice with remaining sugar.
Pour over bread in pan when removed from oven. Let set for 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: apple scallops
directions: Put sliced apples in baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix flour, sugar, butter and nuts until crumbly. Sprinkle on top and bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Blend in pulp. Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: veal piccata
directions: On cutting board, with meat mallet, pound veal cutlets to 1/8-inch thickness.
Coat with flour, shaking off excess.
In large, nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, heat margarine and oil.
Add cutlets and brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except water to skillet.
Cook, stirring frequently, about 2 minutes.
Return veal to skillet; add water.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until veal is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked catfish parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Set aside. Combine milk and egg.
Dip fish fillets in milk and egg mixture, then dredge in flour mixture.
Arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Drizzle melted margarine over fillets and sprinkle with almonds. Bake in a 350° oven uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: no meat macaroni dinner
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over Fritos.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saut onion, chilies and garlic in oil until soft.
Add the remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese.	Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer covered for 1 hour.
Add tortillas and cheese and simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: grandma anna's chicken gumbo
directions: Cook the chicken about 1 hour in 2-quarts of water with 1 cup diced celery in it.
Salt slightly.
Let cool.
Take meat from bones.
Cut in small pieces.
Be sure there are 2 quarts of liquid left.
If not, add enough so there are 2 quarts.
Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes to strengthen taste of broth.
Make a roux of 5 tablespoons oil and 10 tablespoons flour.
Use low heat; brown to dark brown, being careful not to burn it.
When color is light chocolate color, add 2 onions which have been chopped fine and 1 cup okra, cut very fine.
Let cook about 10 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add this to the liquid or broth of the chicken.
Let cook 15 minutes, then add chopped chicken.
Continue 10 more minutes on slow heat.
Last, add 2 level tablespoonfuls gumbo file to gumbo while boiling.
Mix well.
Turn off heat.
Do not boil again.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add soda, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Fold in bananas, walnuts and vanilla.

title: spaghetti pomodoro(our favorite!)
directions: Put on water to boil (and when boiling put in spaghetti). Meanwhile, saute onions in olive oil until translucent.
Add the tomatoes, basil and salt, and simmer until spaghetti is cooked. (Always prepare this sauce in an open skillet.)
Serve the sauce on the drained spaghetti, topping each with a sprig of fresh basil.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and buttermilk. Mix.
Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix together until smooth. May be kneaded and may need a 1/4 cup more flour. Let rise for 10 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, debone and dice.
In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add stewed tomatoes, shredding the tomatoes with your fingers.
Add to mixture 1 pound grated Cheddar cheese slowly and stirring as you add over low heat.
Add chicken to cheese and tomato mixture.
Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain vermicelli and place back in the large pot it was cooked in.
Pour in cheese/tomato mixture and stir well.
Ready to serve.

title: fake fudge
directions: Sift the powdered sugar into a large bowl with cocoa and pecans.
Slowly melt cheese with milk.
Pour over dry mixture. Add vanilla; mix well and fast.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet; cut into squares.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour muffin pans. Thoroughly combine flour, apples, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Stir in oil, nuts and vanilla.
Divide batter among muffin pans (fill each 1/2 to 2/3).
Bake about 30 minutes (until toothpick placed in center of muffin comes out clean). Makes 2 dozen.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Cut cauliflower in little pieces and spread over lettuce.
Crumble bacon into small pieces and spread over cauliflower.
Chop red onion and spread over bacon (however much you want).
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar and spread over entire salad, making sure lettuce is covered.
Grate American cheese and sprinkle over Miracle Whip spread.
Sprinkle a little bit of lettuce over cheese and some red onion.

title: shekh mehshee(stuffed eggplant)
directions: Wash the eggplants and remove the green tops.
Core them, using a coring knife (chop and save the core material).
Set aside.
In a medium size bowl, mix the ground lamb (or beef), onion, spice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
With a teaspoon, fill each eggplant with the meat mixture.
Press stuffing in well.
On a cooking sheet lined with greased aluminum foil, place the chopped core material and the stuffed eggplants in rows.
Lightly brush eggplants with vegetable oil.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until soft.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with cracker crumbs. Flatten in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5-10 minutes.
Cool

title: fool proof pie crust
directions: With a fork mix together first four ingredients.
In a separate dish beat together the vinegar, egg and water.
Combine the two with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
With your hands mold dough into a ball.
Chill for 15 minutes before rolling into shape.
Makes 3-4 pie crusts.
Store in refrigerator or freeze.

title: dreaming icing
directions: Mix pudding (you choose flavor). Add milk until blended.
Mix in Cool Whip. Spread over cool cake.

title: mustard sauce(for hamburger steak)
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter until lightly brown.
Add bouillon, mustard and salt.
Simmer about 15 minutes and serve over hamburger steak.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper in skillet until meat is lightly browned.
Pour off excess fat.
Add catsup, water, mustard, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini with pasta
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until soft.
Add zucchini, basil, salt and pepper and saute in frying pan until cooked, but firm under medium heat.
Combine pasta and zucchini in larger pan over low-medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add grated Parmesan cheese.
Mix through and serve immediately.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite-size pieces; set aside.
In medium saucepan over medium heat in melted margarine, cook green onions 2 minutes; stir.
Stir in flour; cook until bubbly.
Gradually stir in mixture broth and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat 10 minutes until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.
Only 88 calories per serving.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour in large bowl.
Put butter, oil and cocoa in pot and bring to boil.
Pour over dry mixture and beat well. Mix together buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into first mixture and turn into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 pan.	Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Start preparing icing 5 minutes before cake is done.
Put rest of ingredients, except 3x sugar, into pan and bring to boil.
Pour over sugar and beat well.
Pour over cake while hot.	Cut in squares to serve.

title: plantation casserole
directions: Layer Rice Krispies, sausage, rice and grated cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, soup and milk.
Pour over mixture. Punch holes in mixture (I use handle of wooden spoon).
Sprinkle last 1/2 cup Rice Krispies on top.
Refrigerate overnight, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch oblong pan with Pam spray.
Spread chopped nuts to cover bottom of pan.
Spread coconut on top of nuts.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Set aside while you mix melted margarine and softened cream cheese. Blend in box of powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour this mixture over batter pouring back and forth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cake rises up and falls in some places and looks like earth after a quake!

title: quick hot dog casserole
directions: Melt butter and add flour until blended.
Stir in milk slowly.
Bring to a boil.
Add seasonings.
Add worcestershire sauce and mix with green beans and hot dogs in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30-40 minutes.

title: seafood fettuccine
directions: In a large pan melt butter over medium heat.
Add garlic and carrot; saute.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend in half and half and milk.
Stir in parsley and basil.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in shrimp and scallops. Increase temperature to medium-high.
Cook about 8 minutes or until seafood is opaque, stirring frequently.
Stir in cooked fettuccine.
Toss to coat.
Heat through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter.
Add cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in vinegar.
Let sauce boil.
Add beets and salt.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes; add salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, stirring well. Put in large baking pan, large enough to allow for stirring.
Bake 45 minutes in a 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning (fix according to directions).

Cut burritos in 1/2; layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 1/2 burritos, 1/2 refried beans, 1/2 hamburger mixture, 1 jar salsa, 1/2 chopped onion, 1 cup of each cheese and repeat. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Top with sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: greasepaint - formula for makeup
directions: Using rubber spatula, blend the first 3 ingredients on a white plate to form smooth paste.
Add 3 or 4 drops glycerin for a creamy consistency.
The yield should be enough for a child's face.
Using fingers, stroke in one directions, spreading mixture over face.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture and stir just enough to blend.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Melt butter.
Add crushed cornflakes.
Mix sugar, spices and lemon rind in a separate bowl.
Put 1/4 of crushed flakes in the bottom of a buttered dish, then 1/2 of the apples.
Sprinkle with the sugar and spices.
Add another quarter of the flakes, remainder of the apples, sugar and spices.
Sprinkle lemon juice over this, then the water.
Put the rest of the flakes over top. Cover closely; bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and brown quickly.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into cooled baked pastry or graham cracker crust and chill. Will keep several days.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Remove bone and flake salmon.
Combine salmon, cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke.
Mix. Chill several hours.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Add water to potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make white sauce with oleo, flour and milk.
Add cheese, stir until melted. Add undrained vegetables.
Heat but do not boil.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Combine mustard, butter and poppy seeds. Mix well. Cut rolls in half. Spread mixture on each side. Place small amount of ham and cheese on bottom of each roll. Cover with top half of rolls. Wrap with tin foil. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts. Makes 3 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: oysters foster
directions: Make a small amount of roux and set aside.
In separate pan saute garlic in butter for about 5 minutes.
Stir in champagne, cream and juice of oysters; simmer 5 minutes.
Put in oysters and lay spinach on top.
Cover and simmer just until spinach is wilted. (Do not overcook, oysters will get tough.)
Take spinach out 1st, spreading it on serving dish.
Lay oysters on top.
Add roux to remaining sauce to thicken.
Spread sauce over all and serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Bring chicken and first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Strain liquid and I use this instead of water to cook rice.
Saute mushrooms in butter and mix with soup and sour cream.
Add rice and chicken. Put in a 3-quart casserole or 2 (1 1/2-quart) casserole dishes. Sprinkle with slivered almonds and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade onion soup
directions: Saut onions in butter about 10 minutes to golden, stirring so as not to burn. Add flour and stir well. Combine the hot water and bouillon cubes, then gradually add to the onions while stirring. Simmer over low heat about 30 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions, pepper and pimento in butter 5 to 6 minutes. Pour into 8-inch greased baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk and salt. Sprinkle cheese evenly over onion mixture.
Pour egg and milk mixture over all.
Top with broken crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: ham and creamy potato scallops
directions: Cool and peel potatoes; slice 1/4 inch thick.
Spread in greased, 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour until well blended.
Add onion, celery, ham, broth, mayonnaise and cheese spread; cook until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Beat egg yolks and 2 egg whites and add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add milk gradually, then stir in melted butter.
Pour into crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Beat 2 egg whites and add sugar.
Spread meringue on pie and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Depending on the size of bowl or amount you want to make is how you go by the number of cucumbers and onions you want to use. Also the size of each would be taken into consideration.
You slice the cucumbers and onions in your container and use enough sour cream to form a consistency to hold them together.
Salt and pepper to season.
After it sets a while, juice will form from the cucumbers.
It can be stirred in or if it might make it too juicy, spoon some of the juice off if it comes to the top.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in skillet until thick.
Serve over biscuits.

title: spaghetti and meatball stew
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, combine milk and egg whites; blend well.
Stir in turkey, bread crumbs, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned and thoroughly cooked.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer over low heat until achieving desired consistency.
Chill before serving.

title: cowboy rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Brown hamburger and drain. Mix all ingredients except cheese and pour into casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and condensed milk.
Add evaporated milk. Put peaches in blender and puree, then add to milk mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in freezer and fill to line with sweet milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: chicken mole
directions: Clean and cut the chicken in portions; place in a large kettle and stew until tender.
Remove the seeds and veins from the chilies and saute them in hot butter until soft; then cover with hot water and set aside until ready to use.
Heat more butter and saute the onion, garlic, sesame seed and almonds (cut in slivers). While these are cooking, toast the hard roll and brown the tortilla in butter.

Drain the chilies thoroughly and combine with the sauteed onion mixture, the toasted roll and tortilla which have been broken in small pieces, the pimientos, clove, cinnamon, anise seed and raisins; grind mixture until it is very fine.
Then add the tomatoes which have been seeded and forced through a sieve.
Mix thoroughly.

title: breakfast
directions: Brown sausage, break up and drain. Beat eggs and milk well. Break up and drop into egg mixture.
Add grated cheese and crumbled sausage.
Pour into greased pans and refrigerate. Take out of refrigerator ahead of cooking if you want it to cook quicker.
Serves 20. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix oleo, peanut butter and vanilla well and add graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Drop on waxed paper.
Refrigerate. Makes 90.

title: corn bread bake
directions: Coarsely shred enough zucchini to make 1/3 cup; set aside. Cut remaining zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
In a 10-inch skillet, brown sausage.
Remove sausage from skillet; reserve drippings.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Place 1/2 stick margarine sliced in bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/2 of crushed cracker crumbs.
Place bite size pieces of chicken over this.
Combine milk, sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken. Add final layer of crumbs.
Slice other 1/2 of margarine over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Cook the garlic, rosemary leaves and onions in the oleo until onions are clear.
Brown the ground beef in a separate pan. Add to the first mixture. Add the sherry or cooking wine. Add the tomatoes and water.
Cook until thick, 2 hours slowly, uncovered. Cook the spaghetti.
Grease casserole dish and layer the spaghetti, sauce, mushroom soup, cheese, and olives.
Cook 20 minutes at 325°.

title: mocha nut fudge
directions: Dissolve coffee in water, then combine with sugar in deep, heavy pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, to soft-ball stage (235 degrees).
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool, without stirring, to lukewarm.
Beat until thick and creamy; mix in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan and chill. Cut into squares.

title: julie's toffee
directions: Melt butter and then add next 3 ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally (or all the time) until 300°, using candy thermometer.
Quickly pour into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Lay 6 Hershey bars on top and spread with knife.
Nuts on top are optional.

title: river oaks brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch metal pan.
Line with parchment paper.
In bowl, sift together cocoa and flour.
In large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Stir in vanilla. Add to cocoa and flour.
Beat until evenly distributed.
Add nuts. Bake 50 minutes.
Brownies will be slightly moist.
Let cool in pan.
Invert pan.
Turn right side up.
Cut into bars.

title: beer and beef
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 300° about 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add pumpkin and egg, mix well.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: In saucepan simmer potatoes, salt and water until tender. Drain.
Reserve water.
Add more water to make 2 cups.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg to water; set aside.
Melt margarine in 3-quart baking dish.
Cut shortening into flour; add milk and stir only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Place potatoes in pan with melted butter.
Spoon crust onto potatoes.
Pour sugar water slowly over crust.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: vinegar dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar.
Shake well and store.

title: cheddar twists
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat water and milk until very warm (120° to 130°). Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in cheese and enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cover and let rest on floured surface 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces. Roll each piece to 14-inch ropes.
Fold each rope in half and pinch ends to seal.
Twist each rope two to three times.
Place on large greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm, draft free place until doubled in size.
Cover and let rise in warm, draft free place until double in sized, about 20 to 40 minutes. Brush with egg white mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy or sesame seed or Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking sheet and let cool on wire racks.

title: peachy cream cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and extract.
Spread about 1/3 of the filling on bottom crust.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: nell's banana pudding
directions: Make the pudding according to the recipe on the box, but use only 1/2 amount of milk called for.
Add sour cream to pudding. Add Cool Whip to mixture.
Layer a 9-inch dish with vanilla wafers and pour mixture over wafers.
Continue layers and top with vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Stir in fruit until well blended.
Fold in nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and freeze.
Makes 1 large or 2 small salads.

title: "no peek meatballs"
directions: Mix all ingredients except gravy and make into balls.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan and pour gravy over the top.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
No peek!

title: summer cooler punch
directions: Recipe may be doubled.

title: beans and meat
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion and bell pepper.
Mix beans with all other ingredients.
Add meat mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a glass dish.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pans.
Mix flour, sugar, nonfat dry milk, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
In small bowl, beat eggs, oil, melted butter and vanilla with electric mixer to blend well.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture only until just blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon batter into prepared pans.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until browned and knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain well.
Saute vegetables, then add water, soup and rice.
Pour in greased casserole and sprinkle heavily with slivered almonds.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: layered delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Cream butter and flour.
Add pecans.
Pat into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine together.
Add powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Drop peanut butter balls into chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper or aluminum foil.

title: "wild bill's" deer gumbo
directions: To form roux, mix flour and oil; cook on low heat until dark brown.
Boil venison until tender.
Saute onions, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Combine roux, venison, vegetables, spices, tomatoes, water and beef broth in large pot.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 hour, stirring regularly.
Add Cajun seasoning to taste.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: ellie cox's lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper; salt and pepper, then drain grease.
Mix regular sized can stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste and three cans water and McCormick spaghetti mix. Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add this to meat.
While tomato mixture is cooking, put noodles in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salad oil (to prevent sticking) for approximately 10 minutes.
Put in baking dish (13 x 9-inch) about 1/2 of tomato-meat mixture, sprinkle Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese, then add noodles.
Add remainder tomato-meat mixture and finish with the cheeses on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese fancy chop suey(authentic)
directions: Since rice is the most important ingredient in South China menus, the average person will eat about 1/2 to 1 cup uncooked or 1 to 2 cups cooked rice with other food served at the meal.
Use this ratio when cooking:
1/2 cup uncooked = 1 cup cooked rice. To prepare for 4 to 6 people, measure 2 to 4 cups (or more) of raw uncooked short/medium grain rice.
Do not use any other kind for authentic Chinese rice; the grains should stick together rather than separate.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon; add clam juice and vegetables.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Mix flour and milk to a paste and add.
When heated through add clams, half & half, salt and pepper.
Heat to a simmer.
Let stand ten minutes and serve.

title: maria's saucy dip
directions: Mix
all ingredients and heat.	Pour into chafing dish. Serve with large corn chips.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Beat all together.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 10 minutes.
Serve with butter and syrup. Makes two or three portions.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter or margarine. Beat the eggs first and then add to butter or margarine. Add the onion, both cans of corn, the bread mix and the cheese, mixing well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 to 55 minutes. Test for doneness. Don't overbake.

title: banana bread
directions: Put butter, sugar and eggs in large mixing bowl and beat well. Add bananas and 1/2 cup flour, beating well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Bake in a well oiled loaf pan about 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix in order.
Place in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake 40-45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked gouda(appetizer)
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and seal all seams together by pinching and patting.
Spread mustard over sealed crescent rolls.
Remove wax cover from Gouda and place cheese in center of crescent rolls. Bring corners of dough up and over Gouda, gathering edges and making sure none of the seams come open.
Brush top of dough with egg white and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake according to directions on crescent roll can.
Serve with crackers, if desired.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Line cupcake pan with paper baking cups.
In a large bowl, mix cake, water, oil and eggs.
Fill cups to half full.
Place ice cream cones upside down on batter in each cup.
