Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan; cool completely.
Remove paper baking cups.
Frost cake and decorate with sprinkles.

title: chocolate caramel goodies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; cook over low heat until melted.
Set aside.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook 3 layers at 300° to 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef and bacon with a little oil and then mix well with all the remaining ingredients.
Transfer to a large casserole or baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a bowl, beat together butter, sugar and almond extract until mixture is light and creamy.
Separate eggs and set the whites aside.
Beat the egg yolks into the batter and set aside. In another bowl, sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to the batter alternately with strawberries. Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter.
Pour the batter into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Let it cool in the pan, then turn it out on a rack to finish cooling.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, evaporated milk and butter on low heat for 5 minutes at 237°.
Add Marshmallow Creme, white chocolate, pecans and cherries.
Mix and put in buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: chipped beef and cream cheese party dip
directions: Blend together first 4 ingredients.
Add chopped green pepper, onion flakes and garlic salt.
Heat nuts in melted butter and sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm from plate with assorted crackers.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat.
Pour over shredded beef and stir in.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients. About halfway through cooking, add ketchup on top of meat loaf. Cook remaining time. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch in a medium saucepan.
Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until filling boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Carefully press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling.
Cool.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into very hot iron skillet, well-greased.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Put seasoned flour into bag.
Shake chicken pieces in bag to coat.
Heat butter and oil in skillet; brown chicken pieces. Drain oranges; reserve juice.
Mix juice with lemon and orange juices, honey, soy sauce and ginger.
Pour sauce over chicken in skillet.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
When chicken is fork-tender, add oranges.
Simmer just 5 minutes more.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Melt oleo in a large frying pan and saute chopped onions slightly.
Add ground ham and garlic.
Brown slightly.
Stir in flour and cook thoroughly (a few minutes).
Add broth, parsley and sauerkraut.
Cook a few minutes more.
This should form a stiff paste.
Chill in bowl and then form into one-inch balls.
To bread them, dip in flour, then egg mixture of 1 egg and 1/4 cup milk, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot fat (375°) until lightly brown. Makes 45 to 50.

title: salmon log appetizer
directions: Drain and flake salmon, discarding bones and skin.
Combine with lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt, cream cheese and liquid smoke seasoning.
Mix well and chill several hours.

title: sherry-chicken 'n sour cream
directions: Place chicken breasts in 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except paprika; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grilled chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package. Rinse with cold water. Season chicken breasts, back and front, with poultry seasoning. Grill or saut. Let cool. Cut in strips and then dice. Add vegetables and chicken to pasta. Mix dressings together and then add to pasta until you reach desired taste and consistency.

title: mock chicken cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Spray a rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with nonstick cooking spray. In a medium bowl, mix egg white, mustard, water and pepper.
Place bread crumbs in a heavy plastic bag or large bowl.
One piece at a time, dip chicken in egg white mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Shake excess.
Arrange chicken in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink when cut into. Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Heat 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve package of yeast in 1/2 cup of the warm water.
Mix all ingredients together, saving 3 cups of flour to knead with. Let rise to double in size.
Use the 3 cups of flour to knead with and make into loaves or rolls.
Place in greased pans; let rise to triple in size.
Bake at 350° until desired brownness.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and add to butter.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin creme brule
directions: Arrange 8 (6 to 7 ounce) ramekins in shallow baking pan large enough to hold them without touching.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour drained carrots and peas over chicken.
Then pour cream of chicken soup over vegetables. Pour Stove Top over entire mixture.
Add 2 cups of broth.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix together to make a thick crust (1/2 inch thick) in the bottom of a long square dish.
Place in freezer for 5 minutes to harden.

title: breakfast hash browns
directions: Partially thaw the potatoes and break into pieces in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the half and half over the top of the potatoes.
Then add the melted butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: everyday easy broccoli bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of onions.

title: marshmallow and pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: oregano-baked onions
directions: Place onions upright in baking dish sprayed with oil. Mix vinegar, wine and seasonings; pour over onions. Bake, covered, in 425° oven until onions are tender, about 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine butter, sugar and pretzel crumbs.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pat into bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add slightly frozen strawberries.
Cool until this begins to set.
Cream the cheese and sugar.
Fold in topping.
Spread cream mixture over cooled crust.
Pour Jell-O mixture over this after the Jell-O has begun to set.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook whole potatoes in salted water, then shred.
Saute onions in butter.
Add cheese and sour cream until melted.
Remove from heat.
Fold mixture into potatoes.
Grease a casserole and dot with paprika and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: terrific turkey lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of large skillet with nonstick vegetable spray.
Crumble ground turkey into pan; add onion.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until turkey is lightly browned.
Add minced garlic and safranine (optional) to spaghetti sauce and stir into turkey.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove 1 cup meat sauce.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine turkey, seasoning and 1/4 cup water.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Slowly warm beans.

title: j.j.'s elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite-size pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook over kerosene fire at 465° for 4 weeks.
If more people are to be served, you may add the 2 rabbits, but only if necessary.
Most people do not like a hare in their stew.
Serves 3,800.

title: riz au safran(saffron rice)
directions: Saute onion in large heavy skillet in melted butter over medium-high heat until golden brown. Add rice; mix well.

Stir for 1 or 2 minutes; remove from heat. Bring broth to a light boil in a saucepan; add saffron and salt lightly. Add rice and mix well; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer; cover and cook for 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed. Just before serving, add lemon peel and fluff.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 1 egg and cake mix until crumbly.
Put in bottom of greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs until smooth.
Pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Toast bread; butter both sides.
Cut in half diagonally.
In skillet, mix ground beef, onion, prepared mustard and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until meat is slightly browned.
Arrange toast, hamburger mixture and cheese in alternate layers in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch deep pan.
Mix egg, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over layers in pan.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter in pan.
Then pour cherry pie filling in.
Mix flour, sugar and 1/2 stick butter with fingers together and sprinkle mixture over top of pie filling.
Bake until top crust is brown and crunchy.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add all liquid ingredients in order as listed to dry mixture and mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack.
Frost as desired.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Finely chop celery and green pepper; set aside.
Slice eggs in half, lengthwise; remove yolks and mash.
Combine yolks and crab meat, celery, green pepper, salad dressing mix and sour cream, blending well.
Stir until well mixed.
Refill egg whites.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 24 unusual and delicious stuffed eggs.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Chop vegetables and mix with turkey and noodles.
Combine Miracle Whip and mustard.
Fold into salad. Garnish with olives and egg slices.
Best when prepared the day before.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill muffin pans 3/4 full (use liners).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.
Enjoy!!

title: double-chocolate drops
directions: In double boiler over hot, not boiling water, melt 1/2 cup of the chocolate morsels; let cool.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Add slowly the melted chocolate and 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat in flour mixture just until combined.
Stir in remaining chocolate pieces and nuts.
Refrigerate dough 30 minutes before dropping by teaspoon onto baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Good recipe to double!

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix thoroughly; pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Dot butter on top.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in moderate oven until nicely browned and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.
Serve warm.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Combine sugar, milk, egg yolks and shortening.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Put on cake.

title: pudding icing
directions: Mix together milk, vanilla and pudding.
Set aside.
Cream together Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar slowly.
Add pudding mixture, a spoonful at a time.
Bat until fluffy and well blended.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: product 19 cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add Product 19.
Put margarine, sugars, eggs and flavoring into large mixing bowl and mix well. Add flour, soda, salt and cereal.
Fold in chips.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: tandy takes
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar and beat again.
Add milk, vanilla and dry ingredients; beat again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased jelly roll pan (13 x 15-inch).
While still hot, spread 1 cup of peanut butter on top.
Let cool.
Spread 8 ounces melted chocolate bar on top.

title: grandma abie's tea cakes
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add soda.
Add	buttermilk
and flour alternately.
Add flour until it will
not stick to hands.
Roll thin or thick, cut in desired shape, and bake at 300° or 375° until done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix everything together and press into greased 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Cream the cheese spread, margarine and egg with a mixer.
Cut small circles of bread with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
(You'll have 70 circles.)
Spread cheese on bottom circle, then place second circle of bread on top and spread it with cheese mixture.
Brown at 350° for 10 minutes.
Delicious!!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp chip dip
directions: Combine chili sauce, lemon juice, horseradish, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Fold in sour cream.
Add shrimp.
Cover and chill. Serve with chips or crudites.

title: creamed potatoes supreme
directions: Combine potatoes, leeks and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add whipping cream; dot with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° until potatoes are tender, about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese; bake until cheese melts, about 3 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Flatten rolls on cookie sheet.
Seal seams.
Spread sausage, potatoes and cheese on crust.
Pour eggs over all and bake 20 minutes at 350° until crust is brown and cheese is bubbly.
Can add other toppings, such as mushrooms, onions, peppers, ham, etc.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Sprinkle vegetables with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling; simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterile jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cube potatoes.
Cook tender.
Salt and pepper to taste. Drain; put in casserole dish.
Melt margarine and, with sour cream and celery soup, pour over potatoes.
Cover with onion and cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add baking powder, vanilla, salt and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon and cook.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to boil and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Brown Wesson oil and enough flour to make a paste until almost burned.
Add to other ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.
While this is cooking, clean shrimp.
Then add shrimp to creole and cook 30 minutes more.
If not thick enough, add more flour.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter and mix in flour, salt, and mustard.
Stir in milk while cooking over a low heat.
Add cheese and heat until it is melted.
Serve over your favorite vegetable.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Combine coconut and nuts and put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch inch pan.
Prepare cake according to package.
Pour over coconut and nut mixture.
Place margarine and cream cheese in a saucepan and heat until warm enough to stir in confectioners sugar.
Mix well and spoon over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't cut until cool.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Beat 3 tablespoons of flour into meat.
Brown in 4 tablespoons of oil in skillet; add onions and pepper.
When tender and brown, add soup, then sour cream, stirring constantly, until well mixed. Cook rice or noodles while meat is cooking.
Serve rice or noodles with mixture poured over.
Sprinkle with dried parsley for color. Fast!

title: elephant ears
directions: Beat whole egg and egg yolks until fluffy.
Add water and salt.
Work in flour.
Roll and knead dough.
Separate into 12 parts.
Roll each part into an 8-inch circle.
Heat 1-inch of oil in a skillet (375°).
Cook until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon sugar.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take out and top with a mixture of buttered cornflakes.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Freezes well.

title: shrimp curry (indian style)
directions: Arrange Chicken Wings in baking dish, As many as you want to eat. Cover with a mixture of equal parts of brown and white sugar. Sprinkle on Soy Sauce lightly. Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: sugar-free applesauce, date, nut cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with cooking spray. Mix flour, Splenda, spices and soda. Add oil and eggs. Mix well. Add vanilla flavoring, applesauce, raisins, nuts and dates. Sprinkle a little flour over raisins, dates and nuts to keep them from falling to the bottom of cake while cooking. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to a boil.
Put in all the vegetables (cukes and onions).
Bring almost to a boil.
Fill hot jars and seal at once. Do not boil, the cukes will be soggy.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Pour cinnamon mixture on top of batter.
Add remaining batter and swirl cinnamon mixture in.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool cake in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove.

title: almond green beans
directions: Warm green beans from a can or those that are frozen or steam fresh green beans from your garden with 1 or 2 pieces of bacon in the same pan.

title: country cobbler
directions: Combine and mix butter, sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Blend well and pour into deep 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine 1/2 to 3/4 cup of sugar with blackberries or peaches. Pour over batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Sift plain flour and self rising flour together twice.
Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add flour until thoroughly blended.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and add sugar.
Blend.
Add this mixture to large bowl and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes. Add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 275 degrees. Cool in pan.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake(mouth watering)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Boil margarine, shortening and water.
Pour over the dry ingredients and mix well. Add 2 eggs, one at a time, and continue beating.
Add 1 cup buttermilk, 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Ice while still hot.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 14 minutes.
These cookies are very moist and good.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine ingredients; cover and chill.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix together.
Bake, covered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not open while baking.
Serve over rice.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except stuffing mix and nuts) together. Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Add stuffing mix and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chinese pork subgum
directions: In a large skillet, brown pork in butter.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add chop suey vegetables, water chestnuts, chicken stock and pork.
Combine cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir until smooth.
Add to meat mixture.
Season to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 6.

title: ting a lings
directions: In large bowl, mix nuts and chow mein noodles.
Melt your chips in microwave for 3 minutes on High or melt in double boiler. Stir until smooth; add to mixture and stir to coat well.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Makes about 36 pieces.

title: fat-free chocolate strawberry brownies(this recipe is adapted from a recipe printed in the baltimore
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Thoroughly coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.
With an electric mixer, combine the sugar and cocoa.
Gradually pour in the egg substitutes and jam/preserves, beating on low speed until the sugar is no longer grainy.
Add the vanilla, salt and almond extract and beat briefly to mix.
Combine the flour and baking soda and stir in with a flexible rubber spatula.
Do not overmix.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Brownies should be slightly underbaked but not runny in the center.
Allow to cool and cut into 2 x 2-inch bars.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
On waxed paper, coat stew meat with flour; reserve leftover flour.
In 6-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Brown meat all over in oil, a few pieces at a time; remove pieces as they brown.
Reduce heat to medium.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in large pan (13 x 10-inch).
Add rice and mix one envelope soup mix to rice.
Add onions and parsley, then chicken. Pour mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle envelope of soup mix and paprika over mixture.
Add water.
Cover and cook for one hour or until done.
Start oven at 400° and lower to 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until thick.
Beat eggs; add to cooled syrup and sugar mix.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 325° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with floured fork to make crisscross.
Bake in moderate oven about 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Boil undiluted tomato soup.
Stir in unflavored gelatine that has softened in 1/4 cup cool water; cook until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Beat until creamy and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg
in
skillet;
add
sauce.
Cook
noodles soft and drain.
In a
9 x 12-inch pan, put layers of hamburger,
sauce and
noodles.
Sprinkle
grated
cheese,
cottage cheese; alternate until all is used, using sauce on top last. Cover with Parmesan
cheese and American cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except chips and cheese, mixing well.
Spoon over tortilla chips in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate raspberry cream cake
directions: You will need a baking dish, approximately 12 x 8 x 2-inch.

title: mom's buttermilk christmas cookies
directions: Cut oleo into flour mixture until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture.
Cover dough and chill overnight.
Roll out onto floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325°.
Do not overbake. Cool and frost.

title: walnut log
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large kettle.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture reaches firm ball stage.
When done, add 1 cup of black walnuts.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Pour into greased pans.

title: cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apple chunks.
Make dressing by combining mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage.
Add apples and celery seed.
Sprinkle with raisins.

title: little smokies
directions: Warm little Smokies in Catalina dressing.
Serve warm as appetizers.

title: good ol' chili
directions: Crumble ground beef into slow cooker. Add beans, onion and garlic.

In a medium bowl, stir tomatoes with juice, tomato paste, water, chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin and pepper until blended. Stir into meat mixture. Scrape down sides of slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or on low for 7 to 8 hours or until onion is tender.
Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese and crackers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Preparation Time: 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together soups and Cheez Whiz. Now, add everything together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour cherry salad
directions: Mix enough cherry juice with cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple, coconut, grapes, cherries and nuts to cream cheese mixture. Blend the Cool Whip with the entire mixture. Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours or overnight will work.

title: country stew
directions: Use large skillet.
Brown onions with beef and juice.
Add corn and peas with juices.
Slice carrots and celery.
Add diced potatoes.
Add water to desired consistency.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until done.
Serves 4.

title: glazed corned beef
directions: Place the apple juice, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, cloves, cherry juice and mustard in a 2-quart saucepan and bring to a boil over medium high heat.
Stir in the brown sugar until dissolved, then thicken with cornstarch to the consistency desired.
Place the cooked corned beef in a roasting pan and baste it thoroughly with glaze.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Baste again and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Slice corned beef against the grain.
Serve with any leftover basting sauce on the side.

title: baked eggplant casserole
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak overnight in salt water in refrigerator.
Drain eggplant and place in pan. Cover with water and cook until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in melted oleo about 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine cooked eggplant, bread crumbs and vegetables.
Add eggs, pimiento and seasoning.
Blend thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: * Mixture of Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses is good.

title: crazy crust peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Fry ground beef with chopped onions and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Add enough water to obtain the consistency you like.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cut margarine into cake mix with fork until crumbly.
Empty pie filling into 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Spread cake mix on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl, beat at medium speed until light and fluffy. Gradually add Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Beat until smooth. Spoon filling into prepared crusts. Freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar, egg and salt together. Add to scalded milk very slowly. Stir until dissolved, then add vanilla. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the spoon thickly. Whip egg whites until soft peeks form. Add enough sugar to sweeten the egg whites. Spoon whites onto custard and gently spoon some custard over top of egg whites.
Allow to cool completely before refrigerating.

title: chocolate uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa to a rolling boil. Let boil for at least 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let cool.
Eat.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: grilled delmonico steaks
directions: Pour the entire two bottles of Italian salad dressing into a large bowl which has a fitted cover.
Add the cider vinegar; mix well.
Lightly season meat with garlic salt, Lawry's salt, then the black pepper.
Immerse the meat in the marinade, making sure all meat is coated.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: loaf bread
directions: Dissolve yeast; add all ingredients and 2 cups flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low setting and 2 minutes on medium setting.
Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Beat ingredients with spoon, then smooth out in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pam's working-woman's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Mix together.
Cook noodles as directed.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: popovers
directions: Grease and flour popover pan.
Pour milk into medium bowl. Add flour and salt.
With whisk, beat until well mixed.
Do not overbeat.
Add eggs, one at a time and whisk in until blended. Pour batter into pan filling three-fourths full.
Do not scrape bowl.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake 20 minutes more or until golden.
Makes 6 popovers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco sauce and salt.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with 1 can of crescent rolls.
Pour in the beef and sauce mixture.
Cover with cheese, then top with the other can of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until well done.
Slice each potato long ways. Hull out inside in medium bowl.
Mix in margarine, milk, salt, parsley flakes and mustard.
Fill hull as full as desired. Sprinkle on cheese.
Broil until golden brown.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Mix all ingredients at room temperature.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve as a spread on assorted crackers.

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple, saving juice. Mix juice, flour and sugar; set aside. Lay pineapple in bottom of dish and cover with cheese. Pour juice mixture over cheese. Melt butter. Mix with crushed crackers. Crumble cracker mixture over cheese layer. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Mix sugar and juice together; pour over ham.
Place pineapple slices over ham.
Wrap in foil and place in baking dish.
Turn oven to 250° and bake all night.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Add molasses and milk; mix in raisins and mix well.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients and blend this into creamed mixture.
Drop batter using small teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in 325° oven about 10 minutes.
This makes 12 dozen cookies and they keep well in a cookie jar.

title: bonnie's cheese ball
directions: Mix all together well.
Chill, then roll in black walnuts.

title: bean dip-liz
directions: Mix bean dip and cream cheese in mixer.
Add taco sauce; spread on cookie sheet or plate.
Let set 1/2 to 1 hour until firm.
Spread layer of cream cheese on top of bean mixture. Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine
the
chicken, rice, onion, eggs, salt, almonds and celery;
set
aside.
In
another bowl, combine the salad dressing,
soup
and lemon juice.
Mix the second mixture into the first.
Refrigerate
overnight.
The
mixture needs to be fairly moist
before
baking.
If
it seems too dry, add some water or chicken stock.
Remove from refrigerator and allow to sit
at room
temperature
minutes.
Turn
into a greased casserole and top with crushed potato chips if desired.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy peach cobbler
directions: Peel and sliced peaches into an 8 x 8
x 2-inch
square cake pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: nana rocks
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Will make a workable dough. Make into desired shapes (knots, balls, bows, etc.).
Make 1 1/2-inch size.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Ice with 1 box powdered sugar mixed with bottle of flavoring and a little milk.
Sprinkle with nonpareils.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 3/4 cup oleo, sour cream, soup and cheese together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken skillet
directions: Spray large skillet with no stick cooking spray.
Add chicken; cook and stir on medium-high heat, 5 minutes or until cooked through.
Stir in 1 c water, milk and macaroni.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Add contents of cheese sauce pouch.
Stir until well blended.

title: vegetable burgers(243 calories per serving)
directions: Grind or chop in blender, potato, onion and nuts.
Saute ground mixture in oil
until
soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Form into
burger
patties and fry until brown on both sides, or bake on oiled sheet in 350° oven until brown. Serves 6.

title: diabetic salad
directions: In bowl, mix sour cream and pineapple together.
Mix in dry pudding and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together margarine, peanut butter and sugar until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt over sugar mixture.
Stir well until blended.
If necessary, chill dough until it can be easily handled.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet; flatten with floured fork, making crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Simmer the onions and celery in the butter.
Beat the egg lightly; blend with the flour.
Mix both with the potatoes.
Add milk and the celery, onions and butter mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste; add parsley, a little poultry seasoning and a pinch of thyme and marjoram.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat yolks until foamy and yellow color.
Add butter, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour gradually and combine thoroughly.
Pinch off pieces of mixture size of a marble.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make a thumb print in each and fill with jelly, almonds or chocolate chips (optional).
Bake for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully, they will not turn brown.
The bottom will get very light brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: grits souffle
directions: Cook grits.
Stir in margarine, egg yolks and cheese until cheese is melted.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in ungreased casserole and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Bring water and lemon to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain well.
Rinse with cold water.
Chill.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Place shrimp in a large heavy-duty Ziploc.
Combine vegetable oil and remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over shrimp.
Seal bag.
Marinate in refrigerator 8 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: broccoli with a twist
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Mix together broccoli pieces, raisins, onions and bacon.
About 30 minutes before serving, mix sugar, mayo and vinegar.
Pour over and mix thoroughly.

title: al's chile
directions: *Mexican corn meal, available at most stores.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion with curry powder in oil until soft.
Blend in cornstarch. Add 2 cups milk.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Pour into blender or food processor and let cool a few minutes. Blend until smooth.
Transfer to soup pot. Cook broccoli by steaming or using a small amount of water until tender.
Set aside 1/2 cup of broccoli.
Pour remaining broccoli, one cup at a time, in blender and blend with remaining cup of milk until not quite smooth. Combine with onion mixture in soup pot. Add oregano and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature. Garnish with lemon slices and remaining broccoli.

title: marie's chili
directions: Brown the chuck or round steak on medium heat.
Add the bay leaves, oregano and 2 cups water.
Boil for 1 hour.
Pour the water through strainer into cooked chili meat.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cook 3 hours. May add more chili powder, if wanted.

title: texas egg bake(for large group, 10)
directions: Beat together eggs and milk.
Fry slowly in 1 stick of oleo. Heat together soup, water, sherry and mushrooms.
In large glass pan, 9 x 13-inch, lay eggs, then soup, then Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 360°
for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Can chill dough but not necessary to chill.
Roll into balls and press down slightly with fork on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored "shot" or can add candied cherries, nuts or chips to batter before making into balls.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Place one slice of apple in crescent roll and roll up, place into pan. Mix butter, sugar, sprite and cinnamon together. Pour over rolls sprinkle a little more cinnamon on top. Cook in 350° oven until	rolls are brown.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Place can of biscuits in pan.
Mix together cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Spread biscuits with topping mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip picnic bars
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Mix well. Spread evenly into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: grandmother's never fail recipe
directions: *For Spice, omit cocoa and add 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon cloves, 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/4 teaspoon allspice.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Put syrup in saucepan.
Bring to full boil and boil for 8 minutes.
(Watch carefully.)
Remove from heat and cool for 15 minutes.
Cream together butter, sugar, salt and flour.
Then add eggs, vanilla and syrup.
Beat well.
Line a 9-inch unbaked pie crust with 1 1/2 cups broken-up pecans.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes longer or until puffed on top.

title: chicken puffs(makes 10 to 12 puffs)
directions: Melt butter in 1/4 cup boiling water. Add flour and dash of salt; stir vigorously. Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add egg and beat vigorously until smooth. Stir in cheese. Drop dough onto greased baking sheet, using 1 level teaspoon dough for each puff. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes. Remove puffs from oven; cool and cut apart. Combine remaining ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Fill each puff with 2 teaspoons.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim fat from pork chops.
Place pork chops in skillet over low heat.
Brown on both sides.
Pour rice into large baking dish.
Place pork chops over rice.
Cut onion into 4 slices.
Place 1 slice on each pork chop.
Sprinkle with small amount of salt and pepper.
Cut lemon into 4 slices; place on onion slices.
Pour soup over pork chops; cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread jalapeno dip in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread mashed avocados with salt and pepper and lemon juice over bean dip.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco mix and spread next.
Top with chopped olives, green onions and tomato.
Finish with shredded cheese.
Serve with corn chips or taco chips.

title: egg salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well and chill until serving time.

title: eagle brand pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: banana coconut cream pudding
directions: Mix instant coconut cream pudding and milk by directions on package.
Add two thirds of Cool Whip to pudding and mix well. Put one layer vanilla wafers in bottom of dish.
Next, add a layer of sliced bananas.
Next, a layer of pudding mixture.
Continue layering like this until pudding mixture runs out.
Put one-third Cool Whip on top.

title: ham or chicken puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour.
It will look like play dough.
Stir about 1 minute.
Take off stove.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into halves; stuff with either chicken or ham salad. May also use cheese to stuff.

title: potato coated meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes and butter.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes. Drain off liquid and turn meat onto ovenproof platter.
Spread potatoes and dot with butter.
Heat for about 10 minutes in oven.

title: potato salad dressing(large batch)
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together.
Add slightly beaten eggs. Cook until thick.
If it doesn't thicken; add a little cornstarch to it.
Stir to a boil for a little while; set off to cool to see if it will thicken or set in cold water.

title: judy knight's chafing dish meatballs
directions: Combine chuck, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 50 or 60 small balls. Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in a skillet. Simmer meatballs in mixture until brown. Serve warm.

title: pumpkin coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, spice and salt.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Gradually stir in milk.
Add coconut; mix until thoroughly blended.
Pour into unbaked pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cherry junk
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add the Cool Whip and beat again.
Beat in powdered sugar until creamy.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Top with cherries and chill until firm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat egg in mixing bowl. Add corn, cottage cheese and oil. Mix well. Add dry ingredients. If too dry, add a little milk. Spread half of the batter into greased pan. Add layer of green chile strips and cheese, then add rest of batter.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turkey (or chicken) pot pie
directions: Set pie crusts aside to defrost.
